{"id": "10403", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10403", "title": "Haste (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Haste is a &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;starter Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nHaste is a supportive pyrokinetic skill that allows character to boost either themselves or a single ally, thus granting them &lt;a href=\"Hasted%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Hasted&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 2 turns which increases movement per Action Point spent by 2 meters, 1 additional &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Point (AP)&lt;/a&gt; as well as clearing &lt;a href=\"Slowed%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Slowed&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Crippled%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Crippled&lt;/a&gt; status effects. Since this skill applies positive status effect it will always bypass armour.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinesis\"&gt;Pyrokinesis&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if character is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Fire%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Fire Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a starter Pyrokinetic skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Pyrokinetic skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well. \n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 50 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a supportive skill that provides clear set bonuses. As such these bonuses by themselves cannot be increased, however they can stack with other items, skills or talents that provide them. Since the AP cost to cast this skill is always 1 AP it cannot be lowered by any means.\nThe only way to improve this skill is to increase its range through skills or talents.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell pyrokinetic skillbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met."}
{"id": "20253", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20253", "title": "Hasted (Status)", "text": "Hasted is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nHasted is a positive skill and environmental status effect. Afflicted characters will have increased Movement Speed, AP regeneration by 1 and start AP by 1. \nCause.\nHasted status effect can be caused by either spells or blessed surfaces and blessed clouds. Following list of spells and blessed surfaces will cause afflicted character to be Hasted:\nTreatment.\nHasted can only be cancelled by movement impeding status effects, most notably &lt;a href=\"Slowed%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Slowed&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Crippled%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Crippled&lt;/a&gt;. These effects can be caused by surfaces, items and spells accessible to &lt;a href=\"Sourcerer\"&gt;Sourcerers&lt;/a&gt;. Note that negative status effect will not be applied if corresponding armour values are above 0. This does not apply to character with &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Glass Cannon&lt;/a&gt; talent. "}
{"id": "20272", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20272", "title": "Haunted Keep Expansion (DOS Boardgame)", "text": "Haunted Keep Expansion is an expansion released for \"\" by &lt;a href=\"Larian%20Studios\"&gt;Larian Studios&lt;/a&gt;. \nDescription.\nHaunted Keep Expansion is an official expansion for the \"Divinity Original Sin: The Board Game\" alongside &lt;a href=\"Nemesis%20Expansion%20%28DOS%20Boardgame%29\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt; expansion. This expansion is focused on &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Echoes\"&gt;Hall of Echoes&lt;/a&gt; and theme of death on &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;.\nHaunted Keep as well as Nemesis expansions were first showcased as part of reaching the final stretchgoal for \"Divinity Original Sin: The Board Game\" where they showed an early preview of the expansions. \nThe Haunted Keep expansion can be played alongside the Nemesis expansion which is an end-game expansion and occurs after Act 3 of the game. Haunted Keep has been designed as a side quest that happens between Act 1 and Act 2. Mechanically, the Haunted Keep introduces Hexes and Death Fog. \nHaunted Keep will also have its own unique loot. These items do not have a gold value - simulating how the Merchants simply will not buy these haunted items from you. This results in new items that can\u2019t be sold (a balance problem due to increasing your overall \u201cgold value power\u201d), but will still give you some interesting new items for your current level. Hexes will be the lingering effects that will stay with you at every level.\nHaunted Keep also has 5 locations in total, and you will only experience 4 in each playthrough, as it is dependent on a key choice your party makes during the adventure. Like everything in Divinity: Original Sin the board game, your choices have consequences.\nHexes.\nHexes are the mechanical twist we have in Haunted Keep and that you will carry with you to the rest of the game. Mechanically they are new summons, items, runes and effects that are uniquely positive and negative for the player. There are a total of 8 Hexes, and you will leave the Haunted Keep with at least one per player. As you continue your adventure, these Hexes will give you both advantages and disadvantages for the rest of the campaign.\nHexes are magical artifacts, creatures, and statuses that bind themselves to their owner, providing powerful new abilities\u2026 at a cost. Each Origin will have the chance to have one Hex, and they are permanent statuses that are not discarded. Hexes provide an interesting strategic advantage without being overpowered. A wonderfully creepy keepsake that will stay with you throughout your whole campaign. \nThere are four types of Hexes in Haunted Keep:\nDeath Fog.\nHaunted Keep also introduces a mechanic called Deathfog which immediately kills any living being inside it. Deathfog is an iconic mechanic from Divinity: Original Sin 2 and the team knew they wanted to have it in the board game. Death Fog is an environmental effect limited to Haunted Keep which introduces a new set of interesting strategic challenges.\nContent.\nThis expansion introduces the following:"}
{"id": "20235", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20235", "title": "Haunted Keep Expansion Rulebook (DOS Boardgame)", "text": "Haunted Keep Expansion Rulebook is a rulebook released for &lt;a href=\"Haunted%20Keep%20Expansion%20%28DOS%20Boardgame%29\"&gt;Haunted Keep Expansion&lt;/a&gt; which is part of \"\" by &lt;a href=\"Larian%20Studios\"&gt;Larian Studios&lt;/a&gt;. \nDescription.\nHaunted Keep Expansion Rulebook covers all areas involving the \"Haunted Keep Expansion\". It details the components, how to play the campaign, deathfog and more. Spoiler warning is featured at page 2 due to book being used only when playing the Expansion."}
