{"id": "12369", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12369", "title": "Healing Tears", "text": "Healing Tears is a &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; skill in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive mixed skill that allows caster to emit an aura of healing around themselves up to 3 meters. Any ally of the caster who walks into and within the range of the aura will have their Vitality restored and granted &lt;a href=\"Healing%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Healing&lt;/a&gt; status effect which will restore even more Vitality up to 3 turns.\nUnlike most healing skills, this skill will only affected allied characters. Neutral or hostile characters, including Undead will not be affected. However, allied &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; characters will be affected by this skill, but instead of healing they will be dealt physical damage. \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophy\"&gt;Hydrosophy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill physical damage is reflected back when the undead target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill, however the physical damage will revert to healing if the caster is not Undead (Definitive Edition only).\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into both &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 190 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a any non-source &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks are combined. Since is a mixed skill, traders do not have the skillbook for sale.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a supportive skill whose effects depend on the following characteristics of the caster:\nOut of these, Level provides the greatest boon. In case of healing itself the main factor is how many points caster has in &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; ability, however this also affects how much physical damage this skill deals to the Undead. Note that, since the skill causes physical damage to the Undead it is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; ability whose bonus stacks with that of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt;. In case of &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill the healing gained by the caster from a returned \"healing projectile\" may not the same as the physical damage the Undead received.\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nThis skill cannot be bought or stolen from any NPCs in the game."}
