{"id": "14248", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14248", "title": "Health", "text": "Health or Vitality determines how much harm a character can come to before dying.\nDivine Divinity.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\", Vitality is calculated using the character's &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt; statistic, with 4 points given per single point of Consititution. When equipment with Constitution modifiers is worn, this will also increase Vitality in the same way as if it were increased through &lt;a href=\"Level\"&gt;Level&lt;/a&gt;ing. Armour can also increase be found with direct Vitality modifiers, which do not affect Constitution.\nBeyond Divinity.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Beyond%20Divinity\"&gt;Beyond Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\", Vitiality has a baseline of 35 points and as in the former game, is affected by Constitution. "}
{"id": "3415", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3415", "title": "Health Potion", "text": "Health potions are &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20Consumables\"&gt;potions&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nA health potion is a flask of red liquid that instantly restores a fixed amount of HP to the player character upon use. The amount of HP restored is dependent on the size of the potion. Health potions vary in rarity, with smaller potions being more common in monster drops, chests, cheap and easier to create, while the largest sizes are quite rare, require a very high level of alchemy to produce and can be very expensive to purchase.\nThey can be made by combining &lt;a href=\"Empty%20Flask%20%28Divine%20Divinity%29\"&gt;Empty Flasks&lt;/a&gt; with Red Mushrooms or with Red Herbs and increased in size with &lt;a href=\"Augmentor\"&gt;Augmentor&lt;/a&gt;. They also can be combined with &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Potion\"&gt;Magic Potion&lt;/a&gt;s to create &lt;a href=\"Restoration%20Potion\"&gt;Restoration Potion&lt;/a&gt;s, or with &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20Potion\"&gt;Stamina Potion&lt;/a&gt;s to create &lt;a href=\"Strength%20Potion\"&gt;Strength Potion&lt;/a&gt;s."}
{"id": "11579", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11579", "title": "Heart of Steel", "text": "Heart of steel is a &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;novice Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nHeart of steel allows the target to restore &lt;a href=\"Physical%20and%20Magical%20Armor%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Physical Armor&lt;/a&gt; every turn for four turns.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 190 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Polymorph%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Polymorph Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a novice Polymorph skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 4.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 60 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills, attributes and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell Polymorph spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. "}
