{"id": "4164", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4164", "title": "Hero (Beyond Divinity)", "text": "The is the player-character in \"&lt;a href=\"Beyond%20Divinity\"&gt;Beyond Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBackground.\nHe was hunting a &lt;a href=\"necromancer\"&gt;necromancer&lt;/a&gt; together with some other paladins, but they were surprised when the Necromancer summoned the demon overlord &lt;a href=\"Samuel\"&gt;Samuel&lt;/a&gt; to his aid. Samuel slaughtered them all except for one who he captured and dragged into the realm of &lt;a href=\"Nemesis\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt;. Here he forged the soul of the paladin to the soul of a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Knight\"&gt;Death Knight&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe paladin and the death knight escape &lt;a href=\"Samuel%27s%20citadel\"&gt;Samuel's citadel&lt;/a&gt; together and find refuge inside an &lt;a href=\"imp%20village\"&gt;imp village&lt;/a&gt;. But then they are summoned by the necromancer who the paladin was hunting in the first place. The necromancer wants them to find a &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Crystal\"&gt;crystal&lt;/a&gt; fragment inside a &lt;a href=\"Paladin%20Abbey\"&gt;Paladin Abbey&lt;/a&gt;. Inside the abbey all the paladins have gone insane, but they all regain their sanity when the Hero has removed the crystal.\nThe paladin finds another crystal inside the imp village, which has been driving the &lt;a href=\"Imp%20Shaman\"&gt;Imp Shaman&lt;/a&gt; mad. When Samuel wipes out the entire imp Village, the Hero receives an invention from the demon overlord &lt;a href=\"Asmodheus\"&gt;Asmodheus&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"summoning%20doll\"&gt;summoning doll&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Elder%20Anlokam\"&gt;Elder Anlokam&lt;/a&gt;. Then Asmodheus says that the paladin is starting to bore him. and sends the paladin away.\nLater they are summoned again by the necromancer, the necromancer reassembles the crystal. The paladin and the death knight slay the necromancer and take the crystal. Afterwards they journey to an &lt;a href=\"Raanaar%20Academy\"&gt;academy&lt;/a&gt; of the Raanaar. here they encounter Samuel one last time and with the power of the crystal they are able to slay him.\nThe Paladin and the death knight escape to &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;, where the death knight reveals he is actually &lt;a href=\"Damian\"&gt;Damian&lt;/a&gt; and attacks the paladin. After the paladin and Damian fight, Damian deems the paladin worthy to live."}
{"id": "19643", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19643", "title": "Hero (Divine Divinity)", "text": "The Hero is the player character in \"Divine Divinity\".\nBackground.\nA common person of &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;, they were marked by the gods as one with potential to become Divine. Due to this, the Hero was targeted by the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt;, who attempted to kill them, to prevent a &lt;a href=\"Marked%20One\"&gt;Marked One&lt;/a&gt; from ascending to divinity. Left for dead, their body was discovered by a &lt;a href=\"Arhu\"&gt;white cat&lt;/a&gt; who brought the fallen hero's plight to the attention of &lt;a href=\"Joram\"&gt;Joram&lt;/a&gt; a healer in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;. Upon recovering and waking up in the bed in Joram's basement, the Hero discovered the situation the village was in: surrounded by &lt;a href=\"orc\"&gt;orc&lt;/a&gt;s, with the healers abilities severely restricted due to &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt; becoming tainted. To add further to the village's problems, their leader, &lt;a href=\"Mardaneus\"&gt;Mardaneus&lt;/a&gt; had seemingly gone mad.\nAfter aiding the village by releasing Mardaneus' mind from the grip of the necromancer &lt;a href=\"Thelyron%20Hashnitor\"&gt;Thelyron Hashnitor&lt;/a&gt;, the Hero set to leave Aleroth, however, &lt;a href=\"Seth\"&gt;Seth&lt;/a&gt;, a knight of the &lt;a href=\"Ducal%20Army\"&gt;Ducal Army&lt;/a&gt; was waiting at the gates, seeking the assistance of the healer's with curing the plague in &lt;a href=\"Rivertown\"&gt;Rivertown&lt;/a&gt;. Agreeing to contact &lt;a href=\"Alix%20Eastdragon\"&gt;General Alix&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Arrange%20an%20Escort%20for%20the%20Healers\"&gt;arrange an escort for the healers&lt;/a&gt;, they headed south towards &lt;a href=\"the%20barracks\"&gt;the barracks&lt;/a&gt;, to pass on Seth's note, leaving the knight in the village to protect it from further attacks. Between the village and the bridge to Rivertown, a second attempt on the Hero's life is made by the &lt;a href=\"dragon%20rider\"&gt;dragon rider&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"John\"&gt;John&lt;/a&gt; in a chance encounter; striking the Hero down with his &lt;a href=\"dragon\"&gt;dragon&lt;/a&gt;'s flame breath. Before being able to strike the fatal blow, &lt;a href=\"Zandalor\"&gt;Zandalor&lt;/a&gt; appeared on the scene, eliminating the dragon rider and restoring the Marked One's injuries. Giving the Hero the instruction to wait for him at the &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Boar%20Inn\"&gt;Blue Boar Inn&lt;/a&gt;, where a second Marked One, &lt;a href=\"Wouter\"&gt;Wouter&lt;/a&gt; is waiting, the two parted ways, as Zandalor had a further Marked One to locate.\nReaching the Blue Boar, the Hero met Wouter, who advised them that Zandalor has yet to return from &lt;a href=\"Stormfist%20Castle\"&gt;Stormfist Castle&lt;/a&gt; and that the instruction was given for them both to wait at the inn for him. The Hero, unwilling to wait, set for Stormfist themself. However, they were turned away on arrival due to not having a letter of invitation. The Hero set out to obtain such a letter and returned to the castle, seeking entry to the castle with the intent to find Zandalor with his right of entry to Stormfist.\nUpon entry things did not go as planned. On meeting the young duke, Janus denies that Zandalor came to the castle and grants the Hero the title Lord Protector. Unable to decline with their life intact, the Hero became a glorified page boy, completing inconsequential tasks; including the delivery of a love letter to the duke's concubine, &lt;a href=\"Lela\"&gt;Lela&lt;/a&gt; and finding her cat, Ernie, who is, in fact, &lt;a href=\"Arhu\"&gt;Arhu&lt;/a&gt;; the feline himself attempting to find Zandalor, advising that the last place the wizard was seen was entering the basement of the castle.\nUnable to access the basement, the Hero returned to the Duke, who was about to conduct a meeting with the local leaders. During this meeting, the Hero failed to perform their final assignment as Lord Protector: an assassination attempt is made on Janus, who is forced to defend himself. &lt;a href=\"Elona\"&gt;Elona&lt;/a&gt;, seeing this as a failure on the part of the Hero, convinces Janus to relinquish the Lord Protector's title and banish them from the castle. Elona, outside the walls of the castle, reveals herself to be Iona, an agent of the Black Ring. The Marked One is teleported to her secret prison, guarded by two orcs. Left to a custodial fate, Iona returns to her position at the dukes side; unaware that the Hero would be freed by Arhu.\nFinally free, the Hero travelled to &lt;a href=\"Verdistis\"&gt;Verdistis&lt;/a&gt;, with the intent of gaining access to the castle with the assistance of the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%20Guild\"&gt;Thieves Guild&lt;/a&gt;. Joining the guild, they entered the castle through the basement, where Zandalor and the now deceased &lt;a href=\"Joris%20%28Marked%20One%29\"&gt;Joris&lt;/a&gt;, the third known Marked one are pinned to the rear of the basement by the &lt;a href=\"Death%20Knight\"&gt;Death Knight&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ryu-Gor\"&gt;Ryu-Gor&lt;/a&gt; and his platoon of orcs. Slipping past the Black Ring squad and reuniting with the wizard, Zandalor requests that the secret vault in the basement is been checked to ensure the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20of%20Lies\"&gt;Sword of Lies&lt;/a&gt; is still living within its confines. Slipping past Ryu-Gor for a second time, the Hero gains access to the vault, discovering that in place of the sword is a dragon toy. Zandalor, concerned at this fact teleports both himself and the Hero to the Blue Boar, to reconvene with Wouter and plan their next move. Unfortunately for them, they are a mere moment to late in their return; Wouter is eliminated upon their arrival. As the only remaining Marked One, Zandalor makes the decision for the two of them to initiate the Hero's ascension, by travelling to the &lt;a href=\"Council%20of%20Seven\"&gt;Council of Seven&lt;/a&gt; in order to locate and summon the other six council members.\nThe ascension is temporarily derailed at the Council. &lt;a href=\"The%20Succubus\"&gt;The Succubus&lt;/a&gt; is lying in wait, sealing Zandalor in a magic cage and filling the council chambers with &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt;. After clearing the council and defeating the Succubus, Lucian used the &lt;a href=\"scrying%20stone\"&gt;scrying stone&lt;/a&gt;s to locate the remaining six council members, &lt;a href=\"Mardaneus\"&gt;Mardaneus&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Goemoe\"&gt;Goemoe&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Otho%20Rignaforoixx\"&gt;Otho Rignaforoixx&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bronthion%20D%27Anthalis\"&gt;Bronthion D'Anthalis&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Antx\"&gt;Antx&lt;/a&gt; imps and &lt;a href=\"Kroxy\"&gt;Kroxy&lt;/a&gt;. Locating the council members (and rescuing them), the Hero was only one step away from reaching divinity: the performance of the ritual.\nAs the ritual took place, Janus invaded the council in an attempt to halt the ritual. Although the majority of the council were killed, the ritual itself was a success. Returning to Rivellon, the now ascended Hero discovered the lands have almost been dominated by the Ring, with Ferol itself laying ransacked. Seeking out &lt;a href=\"Patriarch\"&gt;the Patriarch&lt;/a&gt;, the Hero cons him into giving up the ability to become ethereal. Using this power to infiltrate the Black Ring stronghold at &lt;a href=\"Yuthul%20Gor\"&gt;Yuthul Gor&lt;/a&gt;; the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20of%20Lies\"&gt;Demon of Lies&lt;/a&gt; was already in the process of reviving the &lt;a href=\"Lord%20of%20Chaos\"&gt;Lord of Chaos&lt;/a&gt;. The Divine One interrupted to ritual and battle ensues, with the Hero coming out the victor. Although unable to prevent Chaos' resurrection, the Hero was faced with his vessel, a young babe. Unable to strike an innocent child down, the babe into the Hero's care and named &lt;a href=\"Damian\"&gt;Damian&lt;/a&gt;."}
