{"id": "11363", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11363", "title": "Huntsman", "text": "Huntsman is a &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;combat ability&lt;/a&gt;, based on non-magical skill known as &lt;a href=\"Ranging\"&gt;ranging&lt;/a&gt; and essential for memorising and using huntsman skills in \"\". \nDescription.\nHunstman focuses on ranged abilities using Crossbows and Bows.\nBonuses Per Point Invested\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell huntsman skillbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell.\nSkill Tiers.\nFollowing tables and sub-sections show huntsman skills that can be learnt by character if they have enough point in huntsman ability. In base game (without cheats) spells from 9 level onward (Adept, Expert and Master tiers) can be gained only after escaping &lt;a href=\"Reaper%27s%20Eye\"&gt;Reaper's Eye&lt;/a&gt; island. \nEach skill belongs to a tier that is determined through characters level that determines whether it can be found and purchased and requires certain level in \"huntsman ability\" in order to memorise the skill. Higher Tier skills may require more memory in order to use them in combat, this especially applies to spells that require &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt; in order to cast them. \nStarter.\nThis is the lowest tier which contains skills available during the Character Creation and can be purchased from vendors from start of the game.\nNovice.\nNovice Tier skills start to be available once characters reach level 4.\nAdept.\nAdept Tier skills start to be available once characters reach level 9.\nExpert.\nExpert Tier skills start to be available once characters reach level 13.\nMaster.\nMaster Tier skills start to be available once characters reach level 16.\nCraftable.\nFollowing skillbooks are classified as craftable for they can be obtained only by crafting them. They cannot be bought from any trader in the game. However possible to get them as quest reward or find them as random loot.\nBase.\nBase skillbooks are obtained whenever non-source huntsman skillbook is combined with another non-source skillbook. Resulting skillbook will be a mix of both skillbooks and will require investment in both combat abilities under which the skillbooks belong. Example: In order to learn and cast Erratic Wisp, character needs 1 point in both Huntsman and Aerotheurge combat abilities.\nSource.\nSource skillbooks are obtained whenever non-source huntsman skillbook is combined with source skillbook and vice versa. One way or another there has to be source skillbook involved in crafting otherwise the resulting book will be non-source skillbook. Like base craftable skillbooks these also cannot be bought from traders in game. "}
