{"id": "7144", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7144", "title": "Icara", "text": "Icara is &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;the White Witch&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Luculla%20Forest\"&gt;Luculla Forest&lt;/a&gt; in 4 AR.\nBackground.\nAs you proceed with the quest &lt;a href=\"A%20Mysterious%20Murder\"&gt;A Mysterious Murder&lt;/a&gt;, at last you find out that she is the real suspect of Councillor &lt;a href=\"Jake\"&gt;Jake&lt;/a&gt;'s murder. That will lead you to the quest &lt;a href=\"Find%20The%20Witch%21\"&gt;Find The Witch!&lt;/a&gt;.\nHer cabin is protected by a mysterious barrier, so you must find the &lt;a href=\"Barrier%20Removal%20Spell\"&gt;Barrier Removal Spell&lt;/a&gt; to get rid of it in order to enter the cabin. If you don't want to find the spell, you can just kill the &lt;a href=\"Fun%20with%20Fungi\"&gt;two talking mushrooms&lt;/a&gt; near her hut. Without them, the barrier disappears.\nShe is the elder sister of the plot's main antagonist, &lt;a href=\"Leandra\"&gt;Leandra&lt;/a&gt;. The sisters have an inborn ability to control the &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt; - as did their parents, but unlike most &lt;a href=\"sourcerer\"&gt;sourcerer&lt;/a&gt;s, they used their magic for healing. One day Source Hunters cruelly murdered their parents while Leandra and Icara witnessed it from their hiding place. Because of the shared traumatic experience, their souls had been forged.\nThey fled and hid, just living by themselves, tending to the natural inhabitants of Luculla forest and avoiding contact with other people. But one day, a wizard named &lt;a href=\"Zandalor\"&gt;Zandalor&lt;/a&gt; approached them. The trio got along very well but over time both sisters developed strong feelings for the wizard. Being soulforged, Leandra and Icara were aware of each other's affections towards Zandalor. He eventually confessed his love for Icara and together they told Leandra. Grief-stricken, she fled their home and over time their soulforge grew weaker. Later on, if you obtain &lt;a href=\"Soulforge%20Repair%20Ritual\"&gt;Soulforge Repair Ritual&lt;/a&gt; during the quest \"&lt;a href=\"A%20Forge%20of%20Souls\"&gt;A Forge of Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", you can choose to repair the Soulforge between Icara and Leandra.\nAt the time when the Protagonists came to &lt;a href=\"Cyseal\"&gt;Cyseal&lt;/a&gt;, Icara has been captured by &lt;a href=\"Immaculates\"&gt;the Immaculates&lt;/a&gt; who follow the Conduit, Leandra. Leandra helped Ice King &lt;a href=\"Boreas\"&gt;Boreas&lt;/a&gt; seal all other Elemental Kings to bring on the faery world, &lt;a href=\"Hiberheim\"&gt;Hiberheim&lt;/a&gt;, and in return Boreas imprisoned Icara in Ice.\nYou have to free the 3 Elemental Kings who have been sealed away by Boreas, in order to obtain the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Rune\"&gt;Fire Rune&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Sua\"&gt;King Sua&lt;/a&gt;. The rune is used to summon &lt;a href=\"Sua\"&gt;Sua&lt;/a&gt;, who melts Icara's icy prison. After you free her, she accompanies you to your &lt;a href=\"Homestead\"&gt;Homestead&lt;/a&gt; and assists you in finding &lt;a href=\"Zandalor\"&gt;Zandalor&lt;/a&gt; and stopping Leandra. This time you find out that she is a pupil of &lt;a href=\"ZixZax\"&gt;ZixZax&lt;/a&gt;.\nYou need &lt;a href=\"Icara%27s%20Blessing\"&gt;Icara's Blessing&lt;/a&gt; to gain the trust of Zandalor's servants, who will help you access the portal to his house."}
{"id": "12440", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12440", "title": "Ice Breaker", "text": "Ice Breaker is a &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;master Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive hydrosophist skill that allows caster to explode all ice surfaces in 13 meter radius from the caster. The ice explosions will deal water damage to all characters caught in the blast which will additionaly reduce all ice surfaces into water surfaces. \nCharacters without Magic Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Chilled%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Chilled&lt;/a&gt; and suffer damage directly to their health. is the only Hydrosophist skill that cannot cause &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Frozen&lt;/a&gt; status effect. Due to this skill dealing area of effect damage it will most likely reveal all hostile characters under &lt;a href=\"Invisible%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Invisible&lt;/a&gt; status effect.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophy\"&gt;Hydrosophy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill is not reflected back when the target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill (Definitive Edition only).\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 1400 gold. Since is a master Hydrosophist skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 16.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nSkill Modifiers.\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then Hydrosophist ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done.\n properties can be affected by talents, items and other skills.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell hydrosophist spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met. Also note that &lt;a href=\"Lizard%20Dreamer\"&gt;Lizard Dreamer&lt;/a&gt; requires a persuasion check to be passed in order to speak with him, otherwise he (and the whole encampment) will turn hostile. "}
{"id": "17088", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17088", "title": "Ice Dazzler Grenade", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \"\"\nCharacteristics.\n is a throwable grenade that deals no damage on its own but inflicts &lt;a href=\"Blinded%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Blinded Status&lt;/a&gt; (2 turns) in 4 meter radius, if the Magic Armour of affected characters reaches 0. Unlike simple &lt;a href=\"Razzle%20Dazzle%20Grenade\"&gt;Razzle Dazzle Grenade&lt;/a&gt; the also creates a ice surface at an area of impact in 2 meter radius.\nAll characters can throw this grenade. However due to the grenade dealing no damage and only inflicting status effect it is not possible to increase its effectiveness through abilities or attributes.\nSince is a grenade it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Ambidextrous&lt;/a&gt; talent which decreases the cost of using grenades and scrolls by 1 AP when the secondary hand is free. is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Slingshot&lt;/a&gt; which increases its range by 5 meters and by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent which increases range by 2 meters."}
{"id": "12363", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12363", "title": "Ice Fan", "text": "Ice Fan is a &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;novice Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive hydrosophist skill that allows character to shoot 3 ice shards at chosen areas in 13 meter range. Each shard will deal water damage as well as create an ice surface (lasts 1 turn) in 2 meter radius. Note that this skill only creates ice surfaces and does not freeze any blood or water surfaces in area of effect.\nCharacters without Magic Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Chilled%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Chilled&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Frozen&lt;/a&gt; (if target is already affected by &lt;a href=\"Wet%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Wet&lt;/a&gt; or Chilled) status effects for 2 turns and suffer damage directly to their health. \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophy\"&gt;Hydrosophy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill is reflected back when the target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill (Definitive Edition only).\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Water%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Water Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a novice Hydrosophist skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 4. \n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is not craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 100 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves varies. The cost to cast the as a skill is 3 Action Points. The cost to cast scroll is only 2 Action Points.\nBoth the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills, attributes and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then Hydrosophist ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Intelligence provides the lowest bonus out of the three (3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Hydrosophist).\nWhen it comes to enemies they may resist water damage if they have: Water Immunity Status and high enough Water Resistance (which lowers water damage done).\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell hydrosophist spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met. Also note that &lt;a href=\"Lizard%20Dreamer\"&gt;Lizard Dreamer&lt;/a&gt; requires a persuasion check to be passed in order to speak with him, otherwise he (and the whole encampment) will turn hostile. "}
{"id": "12448", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12448", "title": "Ice Infusion", "text": "Ice iInfusion is a &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning source skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive mixed source skill that allows caster to change their summoned Incarnate's element to blessed ice. By changing the element, the Incarnate gains multiple boons associated with it. Its basic close attack will deal water damage. Due to the Incarnate being infused with blessed ice it gains Water Resistance + 120 % but it will suffer from decreased resistance: Fire Resistance - 20 %. Besides Water resistance being increased the Incarnate becomes immune to &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Frozen&lt;/a&gt; status effect. Alongside this the Incarnate learns the Hydrosophist skill &lt;a href=\"Restoration%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Restoration&lt;/a&gt; and Hydrosophist source skill &lt;a href=\"Steam%20Lance\"&gt;Steam Lance&lt;/a&gt; for which it also gains + 2 &lt;a href=\"Source%20Points%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Source Points&lt;/a&gt;. Lastly it will receive + 10 points to &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; ability itself. \nNote that unlike the &lt;a href=\"Water%20Infusion\"&gt;Water Infusion&lt;/a&gt; the effects of cannot be achieved by summoning the Incarnate unto blessed ice surface.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophy\"&gt;Hydrosophy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into both &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 2 free memory slots. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 500 gold. A skillbook can be crafted by combining any &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks out of which atleast one must be a source skillbook. Since is a mixed source skill, traders do not have the skillbook for sale.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nThis source skill cannot be bought or stolen from any NPCs in the game.\nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nGift Bag: Pet Power allows this skill to be used on any summoned creature. This gift bag also shortens the cooldown of this skill from 3 turns to 1 turn. Following table shows what skills will specific summoned entity gain from . Note that there are no changes to the skill and bonuses granted by the skill to the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Incarnate&lt;/a&gt;, likewise all summoned entities gain source skill &lt;a href=\"Steam%20Lance\"&gt;Steam Lance&lt;/a&gt; and + 2 Source points."}
{"id": "22849", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22849", "title": "Ice Rush (Original Sin 2)", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;tierless Warfare&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; released as part of in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; skill that allows caster to rush forward in a straight line, hitting all enemies in their path up to 12 meter range. All affected characters will be dealt water damage. Caster will create ice surface as they move. \nCharacters without Magic Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Chilled%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Chilled&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Frozen&lt;/a&gt; (if target is already affected by &lt;a href=\"Wet%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Wet&lt;/a&gt; or Chilled) status effects for 1 turn and suffer damage directly to their health. \nSkillbook and Scroll.\n is a tierless skill that has no scroll or skillbook from which it can be learnt or cast. \nThis skill is exclusive to the &lt;a href=\"Raise%20Bloated%20Corpse\"&gt;Bloated Corpse&lt;/a&gt; as it acquires this skill when it is under the effect of &lt;a href=\"Water%20Infusion\"&gt;Water Infusion&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Infusion\"&gt;Ice Infusion&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; skills.\nModifiers.\n scales with &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, Level and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt;."}
