{"id": "2244", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2244", "title": "Close to the Bone", "text": "Close to the Bone is a given by the &lt;a href=\"ghost\"&gt;ghost&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Velanir\"&gt;Velanir&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Keara%27s%20Flying%20Fortress\"&gt;Keara's Flying Fortress&lt;/a&gt; Headquarters in the &lt;a href=\"Orobas%20Fjords\"&gt;Orobas Fjords&lt;/a&gt;.\nDetailed walkthrough.\nShortly after entering the headquarters you encounter &lt;a href=\"Keara\"&gt;Keara&lt;/a&gt; and Velanir. He talks to you about how horrible it is being trapped there. You have two options towards the end of the conversation:\nProceed to explore the headquarters, find the five statues (see &lt;a href=\"Close%20to%20the%20Bone%23Map\"&gt;map&lt;/a&gt; below), and correctly identify them to unlock the door to Keara's chambers. If you mindread Keara earlier you've learned that the statues lie. The solution is found on the &lt;a href=\"Keara%27s%20Flying%20Fortress\"&gt;Keara's Flying Fortress&lt;/a&gt; page.\nOnce inside Keara's chamber, you need to convince her to let her husband's spirit go. Tell her that her husband is with you, and convince her by telling her something only Velanir could know. You'll get three dialogue choices that result in the following outcomes:"}
{"id": "12188", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12188", "title": "Closed Circuit", "text": "Closed Circuit is an &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;expert Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sourcery%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;source&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive aerotheurge skill that allows caster to release a small electric wave around themselves in 4 meter radius. The wave deals air damage to all characters and creates cursed electrified steam clouds in its wake. Additionaly caster will be protected for 1 turn by &lt;a href=\"Air%20Immunity%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Air Immunity&lt;/a&gt; status effect which increases Air Resistance by 100 % and grants immunity to &lt;a href=\"Shocked%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Shocked&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Stunned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Stunned&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nCharacters without Magic Armour (with the exception of the caster) will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Shocked%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Shocked&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 2 turns and will suffer damage directly to their health. If character is already affected by &lt;a href=\"Shocked%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Shocked&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Wet%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Wet&lt;/a&gt;, they will be instead affected by &lt;a href=\"Stunned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Stunned&lt;/a&gt; status effect which will paralyse them for 1 turn.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurgy\"&gt;Aerotheurgy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if character is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill is reflected back when the target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Aerotheurge\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 2 free memory slots. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 750 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Air%20Skillbook\"&gt;High Tier Blank Air Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a expert Aerotheurge skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once player character or their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; reach level 13.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 350 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves varies. The cost to cast as a source skill is 2 Action Points and 2 Source Point whereas the cost to cast as a scroll is only 3 Action Points.\nBoth the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then Aerotheurge ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Intelligence provides the lowest bonus out of the three (3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Aerotheurge).\nWhen it comes to enemies they may resist air damage if they have: Air Immunity Status and high enough Air Resistance (which lowers air damage done).\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell hydrosophist spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met. Also note that &lt;a href=\"Lizard%20Dreamer\"&gt;Lizard Dreamer&lt;/a&gt; requires a persuasion check to be passed in order to speak with him, otherwise he (and the whole encampment) will turn hostile. "}
