{"id": "10630", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10630", "title": "Collect Herbs for George", "text": "Collect Herbs for George is a secondary &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDetailed walkthough.\nThe quest begins by talking to &lt;a href=\"George\"&gt;George&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;, who asks &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; to bring him some herbs from &lt;a href=\"Lanilor\"&gt;Lanilor&lt;/a&gt;'s garden. In George's room there is an example of the herb, &lt;a href=\"Drudanae%20%28Divine%20Divinity%29\"&gt;drudanae&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter leaving George's shop, head northwest to Lanilor's home; his garden is to the west of the house. At this point, either go to the garden directly or enter Lanilor's home and ask him for permission, which he will grant on account of &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Rescue%20Lanilor%20the%20Elf%20from%20his%20icy%20prison\"&gt;rescuing him&lt;/a&gt;. He will give a warning about drudanae and its addicting effects.\nRegardless of if he was spoken to, enter the garden to find the drudanae. If permission has not been sought to enter the garden from Lanilor, &lt;a href=\"Otho%20Rignaforoixx\"&gt;Otho&lt;/a&gt; will approach &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; and ask them what they are doing in the garden; Lucian's reputation with Otho will drop as a result.\nOnce Otho leaves, if Lucian wasn't able to collect the drudane beforehand, collect the herbs and return to George."}
{"id": "18745", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18745", "title": "Colwyn", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"The%20Magisters\"&gt;magister&lt;/a&gt; residing at &lt;a href=\"Driftwood%20Prison\"&gt;Driftwood Prison&lt;/a&gt; in 1242 AD.\nBackground.\nColwyn is a magister veteran who currently serves as a jailor at Magister Headquarters in Driftwood. He is displeased with his position and bears a grudge against his superior Magisters because he had served in &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Order\"&gt;the Divine Order&lt;/a&gt; for 10 years and has to serve as a jailor. He hopes he will soon be posted elsewhere where he would be more appreaciated. "}
{"id": "2255", "revid": "25770508", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2255", "title": "Come to No Harm", "text": "Come To No Harm is part of the main quest &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Echoes%20Bound\"&gt;Hall of Echoes Bound&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"The%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;The Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; travels to &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; to recover an artefact made by &lt;a href=\"Maxos\"&gt;Maxos&lt;/a&gt; that shields its possessor from the forces inside the &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Echoes\"&gt;Hall of Echoes&lt;/a&gt;; crafted from the same metal as the &lt;a href=\"Lock%20and%20Key\"&gt;sigil&lt;/a&gt; that will open it. It was said to be buried somewhere beneath Aleroth.\nDetailed walkthrough.\nThe only way to Aleroth is by &lt;a href=\"zeppelin\"&gt;zeppelin&lt;/a&gt;, speak to &lt;a href=\"Sepp\"&gt;Sepp&lt;/a&gt; atop &lt;a href=\"Champion%20Harbour\"&gt;Champion Harbour&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Orobas%20Fjords\"&gt;Orobas Fjords&lt;/a&gt; to be transported there.\nProceed north through Aleroth, up the elevator and continue further north to find &lt;a href=\"Augustus\"&gt;Augustus&lt;/a&gt; outside the &lt;a href=\"Ministry\"&gt;Ministry&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Market\"&gt;Great Market&lt;/a&gt; district. Speak to him to be granted permission to use the nearby waypoint shrine to enter the Ministry.\nHere &lt;a href=\"Zandalor\"&gt;Zandalor&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Deodatus\"&gt;Deodatus&lt;/a&gt; will be encountered. They will ask for assistance in closing the Ministry's rifts. Tell Zandalor.\nOnce the Knight is ready, Zandalor must be protected from getting hit by any monster for a fixed amount of time. For the first couple of portals this is only 15 seconds. For later portals it is increased to 60 seconds. A single hit on Zandalor causes him to start over, resetting the timer; Deodatus will also help protect him.\nThe Shield quest item is received when all the rifts are closed, completing the quest, which also awards the \"Shielded\" &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Achievements\"&gt;achievement&lt;/a&gt;."}
