{"id": "3615", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3615", "title": "Confusion", "text": "Confusion is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills%23Mage\"&gt;Mage skill&lt;/a&gt; that can be used by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nConfusion is a passive Mage skill that adds a chance to stun enemies to other skills. Due to its nature, once taught, it is always in effect. \nNote: The 9 level of this skill is hard to attain as it requires level 47.\u00a0 Most players will not reach this level by the time the game is complete."}
{"id": "11523", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11523", "title": "Conjure Incarnate", "text": "Conjure incarnate is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;starter Summoning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nConjure a personal &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Troll\"&gt;elemental troll&lt;/a&gt; that matches the ground surface it's summoned onto, thus receiving elemental powers and resistances related to the surface. Once you hit Summoning ability level 10 your incarnate will transform into massive incarnate. All Incarnates spawn with &lt;a href=\"Provoke\"&gt;Provoke&lt;/a&gt;, however summoned incarnates can be buffed with various infusions, which will grant them more abilities.\nNote that this skill is incompatible with any of the other \"primary\" summon skills, It is only possible to have one primary summon out at a time, and summoning one of them will de-summon anything actively out including the Incarnate. The other primary summons are the following: \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. Since is a starter Summoning skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Summoning skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well. \n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nInfusions.\nSkill infusions.\nThese will always be the same for all elements.\nElemental infusions.\nThese are applied by summoning the incarnate on corresponding surface or through casting various &lt;a href=\"Summoning%23Craftable\"&gt;elemental infusions&lt;/a&gt;.\nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nWhile blood and oil infusions can be achieved by summoning incarnate on said surfaces they cannot be infused through spells. The gift bag: Pet Power makes said infusions craftable in addition to cursed blood and cursed oil infusions.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell summoning spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in."}
{"id": "11059", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11059", "title": "Conjurer (Original Sin 2)", "text": "The Conjurer is a &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;mage class&lt;/a&gt; mixing support and offensive magic in \"\".\nSummary.\nConjurer is a mage who rely on the power of &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; magic and their &lt;a href=\"Leadership\"&gt;Leadership&lt;/a&gt; skill in order to lead their summoned creatures. Their primary weapons are elemental wands in one hand and shield in the other. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; which are needed to wield said weapons. \nTheir civil ability is &lt;a href=\"Loremaster\"&gt;Loremaster&lt;/a&gt; which allows them not only to identify the properties of found equipment but also to identify strengths and weaknesses of their enemies before engaging them. \nThis identification goes in hand with their starting skills. Their spell &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Conjure Incarnate&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Totem\"&gt;Elemental Totem&lt;/a&gt; allows them to summon said incarnate and totem on any surface in their vicinity. This allows them to conjure water totem to attack their fiery enemies, or blood incarnate to decimate their physically weak foes. Should Conjurer find themselves short of surfaces they may use their final starting spell &lt;a href=\"Dimensional%20Bolt\"&gt;Dimensional Bolt&lt;/a&gt; in order to attack their enemies at distance and create random surface beneath them. \nTheir talent is &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Pet Pal&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to communicate with all sorts of animals in order to learn potentially useful information. \nMercenary Francesca.\nFrancesca is an &lt;a href=\"Humans\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be &lt;a href=\"Companions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Recruiting%20Mercenaries\"&gt;hired&lt;/a&gt; from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. Her role on the battlefield is that of conjurer, a mage who provides support through their summoned minions."}
