{"id": "10722", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10722", "title": "Constitution", "text": "Constitution is a core attribute that determines a character's health. In earlier games in the series, Constitution also defined the character's &lt;a href=\"Stamina\"&gt;Stamina&lt;/a&gt;, however in the more recent iterations this attribute has been depreciated.\n\"Divine Divinity\".\nConstitution affects &lt;a href=\"Vitality%23Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Stamina\"&gt;Stamina&lt;/a&gt;. Stamina has constant modifier of 300/constitution point, but Vitality changes according to &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20classes\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt;. All classes start with 10 constitution. Constitution is a main attribute, so it can be affected by the normal leveling progress. It can also be increased by &lt;a href=\"Charms%20%28Divine%20Divinity%29%23Constitution\"&gt;Charms&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bless%20%28Divine%20Divinity%29\"&gt;Bless&lt;/a&gt;, and various Prefixes and Suffixes from gear."}
{"id": "10944", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10944", "title": "Constitution Potion (Original Sin 2)", "text": "The is a &lt;a href=\"Consumables%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;consumable item&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\nMinor constitution potion will increase characters Constitution by 1 point for 3 turns. If the character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; they will receive 2 points instead of 1. The potions weight is 0.25 and its price is 65 gold.\nMedium constitution potion will increase characters Constitution by 3 points for 3 turns. If the character has Five-Star Diner talent they will receive 6 points instead of 3. The potions weight is 0.25 and its price is 95 gold.\nLarge constitution potion will increase characters Constitution by 11 points for 3 turns. If the character has Five-Star Diner talent they will receive 22 points instead of 11. The potions weight is 0.25 and its price is 300 gold.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of potions and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for. "}
