{"id": "2036", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2036", "title": "Consumables (Dragon Knight Saga)", "text": "Consumables are items in \"\" that can be used only once and will disappear. They consist of charms, foods, drinks, potions, and skill / stat books. Consumables are on cooldown when used (because the character is currently eating / drinking), this is shown on the top right of the screen; meaning you can't spam multiple at once.\nCharms.\n&lt;a href=\"Charms\"&gt;Charms&lt;/a&gt; are items that boost the capability of the selected &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"jewelry\"&gt;jewelry&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Armour%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;armour&lt;/a&gt;. There are a dozens types of charms; most boost the player's stats, but some increase damage or damage resistance. There are five quality levels of charms, ranging from lesser to divine.\nFoods.\n&lt;a href=\"Food%20and%20Drinks\"&gt;Foods&lt;/a&gt; are consumable items which heal hit points (HP). Foods are not essential in the game, but they are quite useful at the early of the game in lieu of using a more costly &lt;a href=\"Potions\"&gt;potion&lt;/a&gt;. Food can be often be obtained at NPC's houses (usually on tables). There are many types of food, such as fruits, cooked dishes, and grains.\nDrinks.\n&lt;a href=\"Food%20and%20Drinks\"&gt;Drinks&lt;/a&gt; typically boost the player's mana. Like foods, drinks give players a little boosting that is useful primarily early in the game instead of using a potion. Examples of drinks include water, beer, and liquors.\nPotions.\n&lt;a href=\"Potions\"&gt;Potions&lt;/a&gt; can be an adventurer's best friend. There are different types of restorative potions, including: mana, healing, and rejuvenation (mana and hitpoints). Others provide a temporary stat boost (strength, dexterity, or intelligence) or armor rating boost. There are ten different grades of potions, ranging from limited to ultimate.\nSkill / Stat Books.\n&lt;a href=\"Skill%20Book\"&gt;Skill Book&lt;/a&gt;s grant an extra &lt;a href=\"Skills%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; point when used. &lt;a href=\"Stats%20Book\"&gt;Stat Books&lt;/a&gt; grant an additional stat point."}
