{"id": "5876", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5876", "title": "Crippling Blow", "text": "Crippling Blow is a &lt;a href=\"Warfare%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;starter Warfare&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive warfare skill that allows caster to slash their target enemy and their nearby allies with a blow that will restrict their movement.\nCharacters without Physical Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Knocked%20Down%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Knocked Down&lt;/a&gt; status effect which will make them incapable to act their next turn.\nSince requires a weapon it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Atrophy%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Atrophy&lt;/a&gt; status effect.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. Since is a starter Warfare skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Warfare skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well.\nSince is a weapon based skill and as such it does not have a scroll. It is also not possible to craft a skillbook.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus %) x (1 + Attribute Bonus % + Weapon Skill Bonus % + Misc Bonuses % ) x (1 + High Ground Bonus % + Crit Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Compatible attribute provides the lowest bonus out of the three (example: 3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Pyrokinetic).\nNote that the reach of this skill depends on the range of the weapon itself. Note that the range of the weapon does not equal the range of the skill.\n properties (except range) can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell warfare skillbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Gareth\"&gt;Gareth&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if his demands are met."}
{"id": "10076", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10076", "title": "Crippling Blow (DOS EE)", "text": "Description.\nCripple a target. Deals 130% weapon damage (crushing).\nTip.\nCrippling Blow converts any damage type to crushing, which is usually a good damage type for which the enemies have low resistance. It also receives damage bonus from high STR, making it significantly better than auto-attack in most cases."}
{"id": "16184", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16184", "title": "Crippling a Demon", "text": "Crippling a Demon is a in \"\".\nDetailed walkthrough.\nAfter arriving at &lt;a href=\"Arx\"&gt;Arx&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Malady\"&gt;Malady&lt;/a&gt; will suggest meeting with Lohse in front of &lt;a href=\"the%20Black%20House\"&gt;the Black House&lt;/a&gt;, claiming she found a way to weaken &lt;a href=\"Adramahlihk\"&gt;Adramahlihk&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce in front of the house &lt;a href=\"Lohse\"&gt;Lohse&lt;/a&gt; has a choice of either entering the &lt;a href=\"Adramahlihk%27s%20home%20plane\"&gt;Adramahlihk's home plane&lt;/a&gt; in order to weaken him or deny Malady's offer and enter the House. \nIf Lohse agrees to enter the plane, Malady will transport Lohse and the party there. Once in the plane there is a portal that can be used to exit the plane, should Lohse or godwoken change their minds, this will however make it impossible to complete the quest.\nLittle further from the portal is the first soul candle. To investigate the candle Lohse, or godwoken have to use Spirit Vision. After finding out what or who the candle is Lohse has a choice of snuffing it or leaving it be and exiting the plane. Should Lohse decide to snuff it Malady will proceed further into the plane and create a path over the gap.\nOn the second \"island\" are two soul candles. Lohse or godwoken can use &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Vision\"&gt;Spirit Vision&lt;/a&gt; to investigate the souls, snuffing them on spot or leaving them be. If they are snuffed Malady will open the gate and proceed further into the plane.\nAt the end of the plane is a cliff above countless soul candles. Malady will urge Lohse to snuff the candles. Once again Lohse can either let Malady snuff them or leave them be. If Lohse is in party, leading godwoken can persuade Lohse to leave or snuff the candles. By default Lohse will always let Malady destroy them.\nAfter Malady destroys the candles she will teleport godwoken and Lohse to the footsteps on the Black House and bid them to kill Adramahlihk."}
