{"id": "12508", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12508", "title": "Curse (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Curse is a &lt;a href=\"Sourcery%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;source&lt;/a&gt; spell in \"\".\nDescription.\nCurse is a special spell that will inflict &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Cursed status effect&lt;/a&gt; upon any target surface or character. It cannot be casted by &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; unless they swear their loyalty to the &lt;a href=\"God%20King\"&gt;God King&lt;/a&gt; whose servants are heavily relying upon this spell, however by doing so they will become unable to &lt;a href=\"Bless%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;bless&lt;/a&gt;. \nCursed status effect inflicts multiple negative debuffs upon afflicted character. Specifically cursed character suffer following effects:\nCurse scroll is a special scroll that allows Godwoken to cast curse spell once. The usage of the scroll in combat costs 1 action point. Like most of the other scrolls, curse scroll can also be crafted by combining &lt;a href=\"Sheet%20of%20Paper\"&gt;sheet of paper&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Tormented%20Soul\"&gt;high quality tormented soul&lt;/a&gt; and various void-touched fish. It weights 0.2 and has the base value of 400 gold. \nLocation.\nTraders.\nDue to the nature of this spell, it cannot be bought from any NPCs in the game. \nBecoming Sworn.\nCurse can be only acquired as a skill when &lt;a href=\"Fane\"&gt;Fane&lt;/a&gt; or any &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; character becomes &lt;a href=\"Sworn\"&gt;Sworn&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;a href=\"God%20King\"&gt;God King&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"the%20Nameless%20Isle\"&gt;the Nameless Isle&lt;/a&gt;. When acquired it will replace &lt;a href=\"Bless%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Bless&lt;/a&gt; source spell. "}
{"id": "20251", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20251", "title": "Cursed (Status)", "text": "Cursed is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nCursed is a negative status effect that can be used on both characters and surfaces. Surfaces and clouds afflicted by curse will change their properties to those that cause as much harm as possible. \nAfflicted characters will have:\nCause.\nCursed can is most often caused by &lt;a href=\"Sourcery%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Sourcery&lt;/a&gt; spell &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; which can be learnt by &lt;a href=\"Sworn\"&gt;Sworn&lt;/a&gt; characters or crafted in form of scroll. Other sources of Curse include Voidwoken skill &lt;a href=\"Void%20Glide\"&gt;Void Glide&lt;/a&gt; which sets Cursed on area they teleport into. \nTreatment.\nCursed status effect on characters can be only cancelled through sourcery spell &lt;a href=\"Bless%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Bless&lt;/a&gt; or by &lt;a href=\"Heaven%27s%20Blessing%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Heaven's Blessing&lt;/a&gt; which is not limited to a character but area of effect, however it is utilised solely by &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt;. Cursed surfaces can be either cleared by spells completely or replaced by using items infused with blessed blessed surface. \nMagic armour restoration.\nCursed can be resisted if character has Magic armour above. This does not apply to characters with &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Glass Cannon&lt;/a&gt; talent.\nFollowing spells will remove Cursed status entirely."}
{"id": "14918", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14918", "title": "Cursed Abbey", "text": " is an abondoned abbey to the north of &lt;a href=\"the%20Farmlands\"&gt;the Farmlands&lt;/a&gt; in the dukedom of &lt;a href=\"Ferol\"&gt;Ferol&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nAn abandoned abbey originally owned by monks who were \"rich, powerful, arrogant and ruthless\". They hired the &lt;a href=\"Engineer\"&gt;Engineer&lt;/a&gt; to lay traps in order to protect their secret documents, to prevent thefts and the extrapolation of their secrets.\nWhen this work was done, the monks trapped the Engineer in a magical cage that fed on the Engineer's life force in order to prevent him from releasing details about the traps. The Engineer cursed the monks in retaliation, turning them into &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt;. They roamed the abbey and would continue to do so until the Engineer was paid for his services. By 1300 AD, the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Crypt\"&gt;remnants of the abbey&lt;/a&gt; lay below the &lt;a href=\"Crow%27s%20Nest\"&gt;Crow's Nest&lt;/a&gt; district of the much expanded &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nMain floor.\nSince the abbey is abandoned, there's lich and moss, garbage, broken furniture, cobwebs and of course, a variety of monsters inside. To further increase the creepiness, there are totems inside near entrance. Undead (zombies and corpses) inhabit both sides of the exterior walls. The interior is guarded by varieties of &lt;a href=\"steel%20skeletons\"&gt;steel skeletons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"lich\"&gt;lich&lt;/a&gt;es. There's also a human teleporter stone in the middle of the courtyard and torches along the walls which can be lit.\nOn the opposite side of the entrance is the altar room of the abbey; in the corner a mysterious halberd, that drains stamina when carried, can be found.\nOn the left the hallway leads to the three dormitories, consisting of seven beds. One room is locked, the key to which is on top of corner room's wardrobe. There's also a library.\nTo the right of the hallway is the dining hall, along with the kitchen and stairs to the lower part of the abbey.\nThe long hallway at the entrance of the lower part is littered with traps. After getting through the hallway, another passage with more liches and skeletons can be found. The door to the west is locked. A key lies near it but it is used elsewhere. To the south is a door which can be opened by a nearby lever. Behind this door are more steel skeletons. Further south is another lever, which opens the door seen before. Behind this door is the &lt;a href=\"Engineer\"&gt;Engineer&lt;/a&gt;, the human &lt;a href=\"teleporter%20activation%20scroll\"&gt;teleporter activation scroll&lt;/a&gt;, a chest containing a &lt;a href=\"Wizard%27s%20Sight\"&gt;Wizard's Sight&lt;/a&gt; skill book (openable with golden key found on barrels outside the room), and a strange amulet called Mardec."}
{"id": "20099", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20099", "title": "Cursed Blood Infusion", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning source skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nThis skill allows to change the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Incarnate&lt;/a&gt;'s element to blood with the addition of new skill, &lt;a href=\"Grasp%20of%20the%20Starved\"&gt;Grasp of the Starved&lt;/a&gt;, alongside &lt;a href=\"Mosquito%20Swarm\"&gt;Mosquito Swarm&lt;/a&gt;.\nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nGift Bag: Pet Power allows this skill to be used on any summoned creature. This gift bag also shortens the cooldown of this skill from 3 turns to 1 turn. Following table shows what skills will specific summoned entity gain from . Note that there are no changes to the skill and bonuses granted by the skill to the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Incarnate&lt;/a&gt;, likewise all summoned entities gain source skill &lt;a href=\"Grasp%20of%20the%20Starved\"&gt;Grasp of the Starved&lt;/a&gt; and + 2 Source points."}
{"id": "17043", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17043", "title": "Cursed Cluster Grenade", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a throwable grenade that deals fire damage and inflicts &lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning Status&lt;/a&gt; (for 2 turns) in 3 meter radius, if the Magic Armour of affected characters reaches 0. Additionally this grenade creates cursed fire surfaces at the area of impact (3 meters) and has a 1 meter explosion radius.\nAll characters can throw this grenade. The damage of the grenade depends on &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; ability and can be further increased by &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; which boosts the damage bonus provided by height difference.\nSince is a grenade it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Ambidextrous&lt;/a&gt; talent which decreases the cost of using grenades and scrolls by 1 AP when the secondary hand is free. is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Slingshot&lt;/a&gt; which increases its range by 5 meters and by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent which increases range by 2 meters."}
{"id": "12449", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12449", "title": "Cursed Electric Infusion", "text": "Cursed Electric Infusion is an &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning source skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive mixed skill that allows caster to change their summoned Incarnate's element to cursed electricity. By changing the element, the Incarnate gains multiple boons associated with it. Its basic close attack will deal air damage. Due to the Incarnate being infused with cursed electricity it gains Air Resistance + 120 % but it suffer from decreased resistances: Earth Resistance - 20 % and Poison Resistance - 20 %. Besides Air resistance being increased the Incarnate becomes immune to &lt;a href=\"Shocked%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Shocked&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Stunned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Stunned&lt;/a&gt; status effects. Alongside this the Incarnate learns the Aerotheurge skill &lt;a href=\"Electric%20Discharge\"&gt;Electric Discharge&lt;/a&gt; and Aerotheurge source skill &lt;a href=\"Closed%20Circuit\"&gt;Closed Circuit&lt;/a&gt; for which it also gains + 2 &lt;a href=\"Source%20Points%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Source Points&lt;/a&gt;. Lastly it will receive + 10 points to &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; ability itself. \nNote that unlike the &lt;a href=\"Electric%20Infusion\"&gt;Electric Infusion&lt;/a&gt; the effects of cannot be achieved by summoning the Incarnate unto cursed electric surface.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurgy\"&gt;Aerotheurgy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into both &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 2 free memory slots. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 500 gold. A skillbook can be crafted by combining any &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks out of which atleast one must be a source skillbook. Since is a mixed source skill, traders do not have the skillbook for sale.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nGift Bag: Pet Power allows this skill to be used on any summoned creature. This gift bag also shortens the cooldown of this skill from 3 turns to 1 turn. Following table shows what skills will specific summoned entity gain from . Note that there are no changes to the skill and bonuses granted by the skill to the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Incarnate&lt;/a&gt;, likewise all summoned entities gain source skill &lt;a href=\"Closed%20Circuit\"&gt;Closed Circuit&lt;/a&gt; and + 2 Source points."}
{"id": "17024", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17024", "title": "Cursed Fire Arrow", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a special arrow which deals fire damage and inflicts &lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning Status&lt;/a&gt; (for 1 turn) if the Magic Armour of affected characters reaches 0. Additionaly this arrow will create a cursed fire surface at the area of impact (2 meter radius).\nCharacters need to wield &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Weapons\"&gt;bow or crossbow&lt;/a&gt; in order to use this arrow. The damage of the arrow depends on: base damage of the wielded weapon, &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and height (bonus from height difference is affected by &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt;).\nSince is a special arrow it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Arrow Recovery&lt;/a&gt; talent which grants 33 % chance to recover a special arrow after firing it. This arrow is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Elemental Ranger&lt;/a&gt; talent that grants additional elemental damage bonus depending on the surface the shooting character is standing in. It is possible to increase the range of the arrow by 2 meters through the &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent.\nLocations.\nCreatures.\nFollowing table shows all creatures which have a chance to drop the item upon death. Highlighted creatures in this table have 100 % chance to drop said item. Note that creatures may drop other items as well."}
