{"id": "5093", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5093", "title": "Cyseal", "text": "Cyseal is a location in \"\". It is both the name of a port town as well as the region in which it is located.\nBackground.\nThe town was allegedly founded by a pair of adventurers and lovers named Cyrus and Sealia, who had discovered the region after leaving &lt;a href=\"Ferol\"&gt;Ferol&lt;/a&gt; and sailing westward. After six months of travel the couple spotted land, and decided to name the region after themselves. The story of their discovery is the basis for the play . Historically the region was ruled over by a royal family, who on passing would be laid to rest in the &lt;a href=\"royal%20tomb\"&gt;royal tomb&lt;/a&gt; found on the &lt;a href=\"Cyseal%20Beach\"&gt;south beach&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn 4 AR the &lt;a href=\"Source%20Hunters\"&gt;Source Hunters&lt;/a&gt; are invited to Cyseal at &lt;a href=\"Arhu\"&gt;Arhu&lt;/a&gt;'s request to investigate the murder of &lt;a href=\"Councillor%20Jake\"&gt;Councillor Jake&lt;/a&gt;, one of the politicians who ran the town. Despite ostensibly being ruled by &lt;a href=\"Cecil\"&gt;Cecil&lt;/a&gt;, the town's mayor, the &lt;a href=\"Legionnaires\"&gt;Legionnaires&lt;/a&gt; headed up by &lt;a href=\"Aurelius\"&gt;Aurelius&lt;/a&gt; are currently maintaining law and order alongside defence due to the outbreaks of the undead and &lt;a href=\"orc\"&gt;orc&lt;/a&gt; raids on the town. Arhu's magical ballistae are also part of the defence against the undead with the machines posted at various points alongside the walls.\nLayout.\nHarbour.\nStarting from the gate to &lt;a href=\"Cyseal\"&gt;Cyseal&lt;/a&gt; beach in the southwest () the path will split to the left after a short walk, taking this path will lead to the harbour. Carrying on will lead to a crossroad, the left again leading to the harbour, the right turn leading to the &lt;a href=\"harbour%20warehouse\"&gt;harbour warehouse&lt;/a&gt;. Continuing on the &lt;a href=\"Harbour%20Waypoint%20Shrine\"&gt;Harbour Waypoint Shrine&lt;/a&gt; can be seen and past this a stairwell on the right leading up to Cyseal proper, the left is the final entry to the harbour and directly ahead is the gate out onto the the orc beach. The harbour itself runs parallel to the main path with a jetty on either side. The east jetty is in the shape of an overlapping \"T\" and \"F\", the west jetty is the shape shape mirrored. On the east jetty the &lt;a href=\"Fire%21%20Fire%21%20Fire%21\"&gt;burning ship&lt;/a&gt; is moored against the main stem, on the inner most landing there is a treasure chest behind a rope, which cannot be reached with telekinesis, however, it can be teleported into a reachable location. On the outer landings the east side has a sunken ship and three sailors: &lt;a href=\"Louis%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Louis&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Philip\"&gt;Philip&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Max\"&gt;Max&lt;/a&gt; who used to be a part of its crew, the west side is &lt;a href=\"Conrad\"&gt;Conrad&lt;/a&gt;'s ship. On the western jetty is an array of crates and small moored ships.\nTown Entrance and Market.\nUpon crossing the drawbridge and climbing a short set of steps, the area opens out into a courtyard with a fountain in the centre; the &lt;a href=\"former%20general%20store\"&gt;former general store&lt;/a&gt; is on the left and &lt;a href=\"Evelyn%27s%20house\"&gt;Evelyn's house&lt;/a&gt; is to the right, directly opposite is the path to the market. Heading to the market on the left by the first tent is the potential fish thief &lt;a href=\"Robin%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Robin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rhoa\"&gt;Rhoa&lt;/a&gt; who is trying to convince him to consider another path. Continuing on the fish vendor is by the next tent on the left and to the right is the Fletcher, who sells various arrows, bows and &lt;a href=\"Expert%20Marksman\"&gt;Expert Marksman&lt;/a&gt; skill books; &lt;a href=\"Kelvania\"&gt;Kelvania&lt;/a&gt; can be found wandering around here. Immediately ahead from here is another fountain with &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Jack\"&gt;Captain Jack&lt;/a&gt; walking from in front to the left where the vegetable vendors store is. Facing the vegetable store there are two sets of stairs: the left leads up to the &lt;a href=\"King%20Crab%20Inn\"&gt;King Crab Inn&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Town%20Halll\"&gt;Town Halll&lt;/a&gt; to the right set; between the two buildings is the path to the Town Hall bathroom and onward to the town's outer path.\nMoving back to the fountain between the fish vendor and fletcher &lt;a href=\"Gerome\"&gt;Gerome&lt;/a&gt; who sells secret maps can be seen to the right and further to the right of him the entrance to &lt;a href=\"Thelyron%27s%20House%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Thelyron's House of Healing&lt;/a&gt;. Beyond the fountain the shepherdess &lt;a href=\"Bertia\"&gt;Bertia&lt;/a&gt; is to the left and on the right &lt;a href=\"Cylia%20the%20Enchantress\"&gt;Cylia the Enchantress&lt;/a&gt; who sells an array of potions, crafting equipment and both &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; skill books. Continuing past Cylia and Bertia there is a set of steps leading up between the Town Hall and &lt;a href=\"Esmeralda%27s%20shop\"&gt;Esmeralda's shop&lt;/a&gt; on the right to the section of outer path occupied by the &lt;a href=\"Legionnaires\"&gt;Legionnaires&lt;/a&gt;' camp; turning right at the top of the steps instead will lead to Esmeralda's shop entrance. \nOuter Path.\nContinuing on instead of taking the steps the path ahead forks to the left and right; turning right to one of two entrances to the outdoor performance area on the immediate left of the fork and continuing along off the path around the exterior of the house of healing is two animal pens, the second of which contains the second door into the healing house and on the left the house occupied by the entertainer &lt;a href=\"Reginald%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Reginald&lt;/a&gt;. Beyond here is Evelyn's house and the route back down to the harbour.\nGoing through into the performance area, Reginald's display, the &lt;a href=\"Talking%20Head\"&gt;Talking Head&lt;/a&gt; is on the right and the crowd is immediately ahead. Going left and between the tents leads to another stage managed by &lt;a href=\"Stage%20Manager%20Chaucer\"&gt;Stage Manager Chaucer&lt;/a&gt;, although there is no active performance; beyond this is the final stage with &lt;a href=\"Cedric\"&gt;Cedric&lt;/a&gt; and exit back to the outer path. Here, it is possible to go right and around the building and up to the east gate, or left then past the building, which a beggar can be found within. Turning right at the cart will lead to the east gate or continue ahead to find the &lt;a href=\"legion%20headquarters\"&gt;legion headquarters&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bairdotr\"&gt;Bairdotr&lt;/a&gt; to the right and the legion encampment to the left. Directly ahead is the stairwell to the ramparts (the path of which heads north east to the north gate) and the north east gate.\nTurning left and heading into the camp, the &lt;a href=\"cook%27s%20house\"&gt;cook's house&lt;/a&gt; is on the right and to the left &lt;a href=\"Selenia\"&gt;Selenia&lt;/a&gt; can be found sat behind the desk. Continuing on past the steps (to the market between Esmeralda's shop and the town hall) there is a chest on the left and two more chests on the right with two keys in this area; there are another two chests beyond the tents behind the chests and a final chest in the far right tent. Attempting to take from any of these chests or picking up the keys is counted as theft or alongside opening any crates or barrel or using the &lt;a href=\"mobile%20kitchen\"&gt;mobile kitchen&lt;/a&gt;s; only the mattresses can be used without the legion taking issue.\nTaking the steps up at the far end of the camp the &lt;a href=\"North%20Gate%20Waypoint%20Shrine\"&gt;North Gate Waypoint Shrine&lt;/a&gt; and steps to the rear of the King Crab Inn is on the left and the north gate itself is to the right. Immediately ahead is the entrance to the graveyard, turning left where the path forks around will lead to a set of steps up to the ramparts and &lt;a href=\"Eglandaer\"&gt;Eglandaer&lt;/a&gt;. Following the ramparts around or taking the path leads to &lt;a href=\"Cyseal%20Mortuary\"&gt;Cyseal Mortuary&lt;/a&gt;'s entrance and the west gate; the only gate without doors. Moving past the gate and up the steps on the other side there is a blacksmithing area that can be used to improve equipment. Passing these steps leads back to the former general store.\nThe Graveyard.\nStarting form the statue outside the graveyard gates () there are 5 dig spots beside the graves:\nMoving in to graveyard proper, &lt;a href=\"Councillor%20Jake\"&gt;Councillor Jake&lt;/a&gt;'s dog, &lt;a href=\"Murphy\"&gt;Murphy&lt;/a&gt; can be found by his grave and the grieving mother &lt;a href=\"Siva%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Siva&lt;/a&gt; at her daughter Leonie's grave. Aside from the mounds for each grave there is a larger mound centre east which covers the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"cavern%20%28Cyseal%29\"&gt;cavern&lt;/a&gt; under the town."}
{"id": "15891", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15891", "title": "Cyseal Beach", "text": "Cyseal beach is the beach south of &lt;a href=\"Cyseal\"&gt;Cyseal&lt;/a&gt; and the initial landing point of &lt;a href=\"Scarlett%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Scarlett&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Roderick\"&gt;Roderick&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nThis tranquil seeming beach became the landing point for the two &lt;a href=\"Source%20Hunters\"&gt;Source Hunters&lt;/a&gt; who were sent to investigate the murder of &lt;a href=\"Councillor%20Jake\"&gt;Councillor Jake&lt;/a&gt;. Due to the &lt;a href=\"orc\"&gt;orc&lt;/a&gt; invasion it was not possible at the time to moor at Cyseal's harbour.\nLayout.\nUpon landing on the beach () the path trails east then due north the wreckage of a ship against the western wall. As the Source Hunters reach the end of the shipwreck a crate can be seen on the right and past the ship the path forks to the west. Heading west will lead to the stairs off the beach, however, heading north will lead the party to the corpse of a man and a &lt;a href=\"Rain\"&gt;Rain&lt;/a&gt; scroll (). Searching the corpse will reveal the &lt;a href=\"Traveler%27s%20Journal\"&gt;Traveler's Journal&lt;/a&gt;. Heading west from here will lead to two crates and a unique &lt;a href=\"backpack\"&gt;backpack&lt;/a&gt; () containing the &lt;a href=\"Rift%20Oglers\"&gt;Rift Oglers&lt;/a&gt;, three &lt;a href=\"Grumio%27s%20Cotton%20Candy%20Dye\"&gt;Grumio's cotton candy dies&lt;/a&gt;, two &lt;a href=\"cheese\"&gt;cheese&lt;/a&gt;, a love grenade and a &lt;a href=\"painting%20of%20a%20landscape\"&gt;painting of a landscape&lt;/a&gt;. Continuing west leads to the stairwell that would be found if one had immediately turned to go west at the fork. One this part of the beach there are 15 shells scattered throughout.\nTaking the stairs leads to a plateau with two stairways, on first reaching this plateau three &lt;a href=\"Immaculates\"&gt;red cloaked&lt;/a&gt; individuals will come down from the north western stairwell and summon three &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;skeletons&lt;/a&gt; to delay the Source Hunter's whilst they make their escape. Taking the stairwell the individuals came from leads to Cyseal's ancient &lt;a href=\"royal%20tomb\"&gt;royal tomb&lt;/a&gt;, the stairwell ahead leads up and towards the river; the rear exit to the royal tomb is by the water and following the river south west will lead to the bridge made from the wreckage of a ship and the two drunken &lt;a href=\"legionnaires\"&gt;legionnaires&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Junius\"&gt;Junius&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bibius\"&gt;Bibius&lt;/a&gt; stand guard with a copy of &lt;a href=\"Crafting%20and%20Cooking%20with%20Maradino\"&gt;Crafting and Cooking with Maradino&lt;/a&gt;. Heading southwest at the crossroads and down the slope will lead back to the water's edge; going due west will lead to the &lt;a href=\"Tranquil%20Beach%20Waypoint%20Shrine\"&gt;Tranquil Beach Waypoint Shrine&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"shovel\"&gt;shovel&lt;/a&gt;. Heading southeast will lead to &lt;a href=\"Ishmashell\"&gt;Ishmashell&lt;/a&gt; (). Heading north from the waypoint shrine leads back to the two guards and a dig spot () along the way to the right. To the left near the wreckage south of the guards is two wooden crates and three &lt;a href=\"branch\"&gt;branch&lt;/a&gt;es.\nAfter crossing the bridge where the two legionnaires are stationed, turn right for two &lt;a href=\"bluegill%20mushroom\"&gt;bluegill mushroom&lt;/a&gt;s () then double back and follow the path west and a battle on the beach below between the legion and orcs can be seen. Before the bend down to the beach there is a on top of the &lt;a href=\"water%20barrel\"&gt;water barrel&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"tomato\"&gt;tomato&lt;/a&gt; beside it. Upon reaching the bottom of the ramp the beach, an orc ship will land with an &lt;a href=\"orc%20shaman\"&gt;orc shaman&lt;/a&gt;, two &lt;a href=\"young%20orc%20trooper\"&gt;young orc trooper&lt;/a&gt;s and a &lt;a href=\"black%20cultist\"&gt;black cultist&lt;/a&gt; disembarking to back up the &lt;a href=\"orc%20trooper\"&gt;orc trooper&lt;/a&gt; already on the beach. Once the orcs have been defeated, head to the left of the bridge to find a &lt;a href=\"stardust%20herb\"&gt;stardust herb&lt;/a&gt; under bush by the city wall and the bridge (), a chest () and a &lt;a href=\"Fire%21%20Fire%21%20Fire%21\"&gt;burning ship&lt;/a&gt;. Crossing the bridge will grant access to Cyseal."}
