{"id": "10609", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10609", "title": "Dallis", "text": "Dallis the Hammer is a white magister general of &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Order\"&gt;Divine Order&lt;/a&gt;. She, alongside Lucian, is credited for saving &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; from the void in 1242 AD. \nBackground.\nA long-standing white magister, Dallis was known for her kindness and incredible strategic mind. However, at some time prior to 1242 AD, the original Dallis entered a crypt and was slain by the daughter of &lt;a href=\"Fane\"&gt;Fane&lt;/a&gt;, who then used Dallis' face to make a shape-shifting mask. In the form of Dallis, she joined Lucian and exposed the true origins of the &lt;a href=\"Seven%20Gods\"&gt;Seven Gods&lt;/a&gt;. Together, they made a plan to purge the world of source. Following the replacement, her behaviour noticeably changed, with her close friends lamenting her change.\nTo achieve this goal, Dallis uncovered the &lt;a href=\"Source%20collar\"&gt;Source collar&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"purging%20wand\"&gt;purging wand&lt;/a&gt;s on &lt;a href=\"Reaper%27s%20Eye\"&gt;Reaper's Eye&lt;/a&gt;, and ordered &lt;a href=\"Sourcerer\"&gt;Sourcerer&lt;/a&gt;s from across Rivellon to be transported to &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt;, where they would be 'cured' of &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;. She also had the captured necromancer, &lt;a href=\"Tarquin\"&gt;Tarquin&lt;/a&gt;, resurrect &lt;a href=\"Braccus%20Rex\"&gt;Braccus Rex&lt;/a&gt; (whom she disguised as Vredeman). Using Braccus as a 'source bloodhound', she uncovered the &lt;a href=\"Aeteran\"&gt;Aeteran&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"the%20Blackpits\"&gt;the Blackpits&lt;/a&gt;. In addition to this, she also learned how to transform into a dragon from him, a skill believed to only be known to the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knights\"&gt;Dragon Knights&lt;/a&gt;.\nDallis had numerous clashes with the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; while trying to enact this plan, however, she eventually was successful in using the Aeteran to drain the source wellspring and killing &lt;a href=\"Alexandar\"&gt;Alexandar&lt;/a&gt;. When the Godwoken reached &lt;a href=\"Arx\"&gt;Arx&lt;/a&gt; and learned the truth behind the Gods themselves, they surrendered their Source. Dallis and Lucian then used the Aeteran to mend the veil, stopping the voidwoken from reclaiming Rivellon.\nVarieties.\nFollowing table shows all the changing stats and abilities of Dallis across the locations in the game. Note that the values are for Classic Difficulty which contains un-modified values of the stats. \nRelated Achievements.\nHammered - Force Dallis to retreat from combat in &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt;"}
