{"id": "3617", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3617", "title": "Death Blow", "text": "Death Blow is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills%23Warrior\"&gt;Warrior skill&lt;/a&gt; that can be used by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nDeath Blow is a passive Warrior skill that gives the Knight additional chance to cause critical damage with their attacks. This skill can be cast only with melee weapon in hand or free hands. Due to its nature, once learnt, it will be always active. Note that the critical strike chance from this skill is added to all other critical hit bonuses."}
{"id": "4156", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4156", "title": "Death Knight", "text": "Death knights are &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s found in the \"&lt;a href=\"Divinity%20series\"&gt;Divinity series&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBackground.\nDeath knights are humanoid demons in armour, that are most notably known for their part in the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt;s army for their role of killing &lt;a href=\"Marked%20One\"&gt;Marked One&lt;/a&gt;s before they could ascend to Divinity. These knights wield a long sword and, although not the top of the demonic ranks, they are often charged with leading missions, either alone or at the head of a troop.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Nemesis\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt;, the death knights serve a master or a mistress and are primarily used as elite guards. Most notably, &lt;a href=\"Samuel\"&gt;Samuel&lt;/a&gt; uses Death Knights as his personal guard, and when he is summoned away he orders his elite guard to capture the &lt;a href=\"Hero%20%28Beyond%20Divinity%29\"&gt;hero&lt;/a&gt; and his Death Knight companion, who is fact the Damned One, &lt;a href=\"Damian\"&gt;Damian&lt;/a&gt; seeking to make his escape.\nBy 1300 AD death knights can still be seen in artwork, but are no longer found among the ranks of the Black Ring.\nArtificial Death Knights.\nIn 4AR there were death knights not from the demon world itself, but created by the &lt;a href=\"Immaculates\"&gt;Immaculates&lt;/a&gt;' Conduit, the witch &lt;a href=\"Leandra\"&gt;Leandra&lt;/a&gt;. These knights, completely under the control of the Conduit were impervious to the attacks of mortals, but with the &lt;a href=\"Death%20Knight%20Bane\"&gt;Death Knight Bane&lt;/a&gt; spell, they could be weakened enough to lose their invulnerability."}
