{"id": "20254", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20254", "title": "Decaying (Status)", "text": "Decaying is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nDecaying is a negative environmental and skill status effect. Characters afflicted by it will receive damage from all source of healing except &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Necromancy&lt;/a&gt;. The effect takes place only if character does not have Physical armour above 0. The only exception to this rule are characters with &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Glass Cannon&lt;/a&gt; talent and characters that enter &lt;a href=\"Paradise%20Downs\"&gt;Paradise Downs&lt;/a&gt;, where Decay will be applied regardless of Physical armour values. In &lt;a href=\"Paradise%20Downs\"&gt;Paradise Downs&lt;/a&gt; Decay status can be dispelled only if &lt;a href=\"Harbinger%20of%20Doom\"&gt;Harbinger of Doom&lt;/a&gt; is defeated.\nCause.\nDecaying can be caused by both surface and skills. On &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; it is the contact with \"cursed blood surface\" and \"cursed water surface\" which can inflict decay upon a character. Other means of afflicting decay involve spells from &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; school or &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; skills. \nTreatment.\nAs with any other negative status effect, there are two ways how to avoid and negate its effects. First its important to keep Physical armour value above 0. Secondly status effect &lt;a href=\"Blessed%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Blessed&lt;/a&gt; protect from being affected by Decay. \nPhysical armour restoration.\nDecay can be resisted if character has Physical armour above 0. This does not apply to characters with &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Glass Cannon&lt;/a&gt; talent.\nStatus removal.\nFollowing spells will remove Decayed status entirely."}
{"id": "9795", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9795", "title": "Decaying Touch (DOS EE)", "text": "Description.\nMake a target decay, so that it cannot be healed by magic or potions anymore. It will be damaged instead!\n100% base chance to set Decaying Touch for 2 turns."}
{"id": "10411", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10411", "title": "Decaying Touch (Original Sin 2)", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;starter Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\nSkill.\n is a offensive necromancer skill that allows caster to deal physical damage to their enemy by touching them (range of the skill is roughly 1.9 meters). Characters without Physical Armour are afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Decaying%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Decaying&lt;/a&gt; status effect that turns all healing, with the exception from Necromancy magic based healing, to physical damage for 2 turns. \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Necromancy\"&gt;Necromancy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill is not reflected back when the target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill (Definitive Edition only).\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Necromancy%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Necromancy Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a starter Necromancer skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Necromancer skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well. \n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 60 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves varies. The AP cost to cast the as a skill is 2 AP and the cost to cast as a scroll is 1 AP. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills, attributes and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then Warfare ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Intelligence provides the lowest bonus out of the three (3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Warfare).\nWhen it comes to enemies they may resist water damage if they have: Physical Immunity Status. There are no actual resistances that may lower physical damage done.\nSince is a skill requiring Necromancer ability to cast on its own, it will cause caster to heal from damage done directly to the Vitality of target enemy. The health received is affected by damage done to the Vitality and by points invested in Necromancer ability itself.\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell necromancer spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. Out of these only \"&lt;a href=\"Tarquin\"&gt;Tarquin&lt;/a&gt;\" is guaranteed to follow the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; as they travel with &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;. \"&lt;a href=\"Jahan\"&gt;Jahan&lt;/a&gt;\" may join the Godwoken on the ship as well if his demands are met. "}
{"id": "8673", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8673", "title": "Decimus", "text": "Decimus is a &lt;a href=\"champions\"&gt;champion&lt;/a&gt; found at the &lt;a href=\"Healers%27%20House\"&gt;Healers' House&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Market\"&gt;Great Market&lt;/a&gt; district of &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; in 1300 AD.\nBackground.\nDecimus is a champion seeking some peace of mind in his final hours because his wife passed away during the siege and he will soon follow her to &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Echoes\"&gt;Hall of Echoes&lt;/a&gt; he is afraid he will not be able to reunite with her. He asks the Knight to retrieve his wife's &lt;a href=\"Livia%27s%20Ring\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt;, in hope that it will help him find her soul in the Hall of Echoes."}
{"id": "9012", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9012", "title": "Decimus' House", "text": "Decimus' House is a &lt;a href=\"Locations%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;location&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Crow%27s%20Nest\"&gt;Crow's Nest&lt;/a&gt; district of &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; that is accessible during the events of \"\". It is situated in the southeast area of the district, east of &lt;a href=\"Henry%20and%20Eleanor%27s%20House\"&gt;Henry and Eleanor's House&lt;/a&gt;, southeast of &lt;a href=\"Crowell%27s%20House\"&gt;Crowell's House&lt;/a&gt;, and south of the &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Secrets\"&gt;House of Secrets&lt;/a&gt;. The home belongs the Champion &lt;a href=\"Decimus\"&gt;Decimus&lt;/a&gt;, a dying man being cared for at the &lt;a href=\"Healers%27%20House\"&gt;Healers' House&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Market\"&gt;Great Market&lt;/a&gt; district.\nDescription.\nExterior.\nThe back door on the northeast side is barricaded, but the front door on the southwest side is unlocked. Near the front door there is a &lt;a href=\"chest\"&gt;chest&lt;/a&gt; that can be &lt;a href=\"Lockpick%20%28Divinity%20II%29\"&gt;lockpick&lt;/a&gt;ed for random loot. The narrow alley on the southeast side of the house is where you'll encounter &lt;a href=\"Tom%20%28Crows%20Nest%29\"&gt;Tom&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Taurus\"&gt;Taurus&lt;/a&gt; to begin the quest &lt;a href=\"Beauty%20And%20The%20Beast%20%28Divinity%20II%29\"&gt;Beauty And The Beast&lt;/a&gt;, possibly acquiring &lt;a href=\"Tom%27s%20Severed%20Finger\"&gt;Tom's Severed Finger&lt;/a&gt;. You'll also find one of the five handles you need to pull for the quest &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Handles\"&gt;Rune Handles&lt;/a&gt; in the eastern corner.\nInterior.\nUpon entering the house you immediately encounter the notorious bandit, &lt;a href=\"Carmina\"&gt;Carmina&lt;/a&gt;, and a handful of her men. Slaughter them and loot &lt;a href=\"Carmina%27s%20Necklace\"&gt;Carmina's Necklace&lt;/a&gt; for the quest &lt;a href=\"A%20Hunting%20We%20Shall%20Go%20Again\"&gt;A Hunting We Shall Go Again&lt;/a&gt;. The house appears to have been ransacked by the bandits, but still contains loot.\nProceed to the northwest corner of the house and pull the lever. This opens the first door in the southwest.\nGo to the northeast corner of the house and pull the lever to open the second door. Loot the unlocked chest here for random loot.\nHead south, looting the small unlocked chest on the desk for &lt;a href=\"Livia%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Livia's Ring&lt;/a&gt; (). This can be given either to &lt;a href=\"Decimus\"&gt;Decimus&lt;/a&gt; to complete &lt;a href=\"Eternal%20Commitment\"&gt;Eternal Commitment&lt;/a&gt;, or to &lt;a href=\"Astridax\"&gt;Astridax&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"Sinister%20Motives\"&gt;Sinister Motives&lt;/a&gt;. Continue to the southeast corner of the house and pull the lever to open the last door.\nGo to the southwest corner of the house and loot the unlocked golden chest for more random loot."}
