{"id": "12479", "revid": "53946974", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12479", "title": "Decrepit Ruins", "text": "The are based in the north end of &lt;a href=\"Reapers%27%20Eye\"&gt;Reapers' Eye&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Marshes\"&gt;Hollow Marshes&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nThe are the remains of an old armoury, cursed by the Source King, &lt;a href=\"Braccus%20Rex\"&gt;Braccus Rex&lt;/a&gt; during his reign. \nNow abandoned, curses remain to ensnare the unwary. The armoury is of particular interest to the &lt;a href=\"The%20Magisters\"&gt;Magisters&lt;/a&gt; of Reapers' Eye, who have been dispatched by &lt;a href=\"Dallis\"&gt;Dallis&lt;/a&gt; to recover its arsenal.\nLayout.\nThe first room of the armoury contains the bodies of multiple Magisters. &lt;a href=\"Sang\"&gt;Magister Sang&lt;/a&gt;, the sole survivor, explains that the lever to open the door has been cursed. The upper section of this room contains a source jar, allowing one to obtain source points in order to &lt;a href=\"Bless\"&gt;Bless&lt;/a&gt; the lever and lift the curse.\nWith the curse lifted, the lever can be used to access the Armoury Vault, where the &lt;a href=\"Corrupted%20Tyrant%27s%20Helm\"&gt;Corrupted Tyrant's Helm&lt;/a&gt; can be found."}
