{"id": "12365", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12365", "title": "Deep Freeze", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Master\"&gt;master Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive hydrosophist skill that allows caster to send forth (up to 8 meters) a small freezing wave that will deal water damage to all characters (including allies) and instantly kill those who are already under &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Frozen&lt;/a&gt; status effect and below 10 % Vitality. The freezing wave also leaves an ice surface which will melt after 1 turn and turn into water surface. \nCharacters without Magic Armour will be afflicted &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Frozen&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 1 turn. Thus the skill bypasses the need for enemies to be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Chilled%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Chilled&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Wet%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Wet&lt;/a&gt; status effects in order to incapacitate them. Note that enemies who have lost all Magic Armour and wind up under 10 % Vitality due to skill will be only afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Frozen&lt;/a&gt; status effect. \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophy\"&gt;Hydrosophy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill is not reflected back when the target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill (Definitive Edition only).\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 1400 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Water%20Skillbook\"&gt;High Tier Blank Water Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a master Hydrosophist skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 16.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 350 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves varies. The cost to cast the as a skill is 4 Action Points. The cost to cast scroll is only 2 Action Points.\nBoth the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then Hydrosophist ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Intelligence provides the lowest bonus out of the three (3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Hydrosophist).\nWhen it comes to enemies they may resist water damage if they have: Water Immunity Status and high enough Water Resistance (which lowers water damage done).\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell hydrosophist spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met. Also note that &lt;a href=\"Lizard%20Dreamer\"&gt;Lizard Dreamer&lt;/a&gt; requires a persuasion check to be passed in order to speak with him, otherwise he (and the whole encampment) will turn hostile. "}
