{"id": "3735", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3735", "title": "Defenders of Aleroth Armour", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Armour%23Unique%20Armour%20List\"&gt;special armour&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nDefenders of Aleroth Armour is a special armour that used to belong to a group of wizards that defended &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; during the Great War and is part of the &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Set\"&gt;Defenders of Aleroth Set&lt;/a&gt;. The set is constituted of &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Helmet\"&gt;helmet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Armour\"&gt;armour&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Leggings\"&gt;leggings&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Vampire%20Mace\"&gt;mace&lt;/a&gt;. It requires atleast level 10 in order to be worn. When worn the armour will boost Ranged Armour Rating by 2 points. The armour has 1 enchantments slot. The default enchantment is Ranged Protection.\nHow to Obtain.\nCan be bought from skeleton &lt;a href=\"Carlin\"&gt;Carlin&lt;/a&gt; atop of the &lt;a href=\"Lovis%27%20Tower\"&gt;Lovis' Tower&lt;/a&gt;.\nSet Properties.\nDefenders of Aleroth Armour is a part of the set Defenders of Aleroth Set which allows the item to gain additional, potentially increasing, properties the more items of the same set are worn. Defenders of Aleroth Armour primary increased attribute is Magic Damage, which is firstly gained by equipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping more items from the set. "}
{"id": "3736", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3736", "title": "Defenders of Aleroth Helmet", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Armour%23Unique%20Armour%20List\"&gt;special helmet&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nDefenders of Aleroth Helmet is a special helmet that used to belong to a group of wizards that defended &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; during the Great War and is part of the &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Set\"&gt;Defenders of Aleroth Set&lt;/a&gt;. The set is constituted of &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Helmet\"&gt;helmet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Armour\"&gt;armour&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Leggings\"&gt;leggings&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Vampire%20Mace\"&gt;mace&lt;/a&gt;. It requires atleast level 5 in order to be worn. When worn the helmet will boost Melee Armour Rating by 1 points and Magic Armour Rating by 1 point. The armour has 2 enchantments slots. The default enchantments are Magic Damage Aura and Magic Protection.\nHow to Obtain.\nPurchased from &lt;a href=\"Locke\"&gt;Locke&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Boar\"&gt;Black Boar&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley%20Village\"&gt;Broken Valley Village&lt;/a&gt;.\nSet Properties.\nDefenders of Aleroth Helmet is a part of the set Defenders of Aleroth Set which allows the item to gain additional, potentially increasing, properties the more items of the same set are worn. Defenders of Aleroth Helmet primary increased attribute is &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;, which is firstly gained by equipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping more items from the set. "}
{"id": "3863", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3863", "title": "Defenders of Aleroth Leggings", "text": " are a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Armour%23Unique%20Armour%20List\"&gt;special leggings&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nDefenders of Aleroth leggings are a special leggings that used to belong to a group of wizards that defended &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; during the Great War and is part of the &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Set\"&gt;Defenders of Aleroth Set&lt;/a&gt;. The set is constituted of &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Helmet\"&gt;helmet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Armour\"&gt;armour&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Leggings\"&gt;leggings&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Vampire%20Mace\"&gt;mace&lt;/a&gt;. It requires atleast level 12 in order to be worn. When worn the leggings will boost Ranged Armour Rating by 2 points and &lt;a href=\"Vitality\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; attribute by 3 points. The armour has 2 enchantments slot. The default enchantments are Melee Protection and Retribution Aura.\nHow to Obtain.\nPrize for destroying the &lt;a href=\"Hellgate%20%28Broken%20Valley%29\"&gt;Hellgate&lt;/a&gt; (West of the Quarry), dropped by the &lt;a href=\"Demons\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; (you have to activate the pedestal 4 times in total) in &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley\"&gt;Broken Valley&lt;/a&gt;.\nSet Properties.\nDefenders of Aleroth Leggings is a part of the set Defenders of Aleroth Set which allows the item to gain additional, potentially increasing, properties the more items of the same set are worn. Defenders of Aleroth Leggings primary increased attribute is &lt;a href=\"Conditioned%20Body\"&gt;Conditioned Body&lt;/a&gt;, which is firstly gained by equipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping more items from the set. "}
{"id": "3728", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3728", "title": "Defenders of Aleroth Set", "text": "This armour and weapon set is available only in the \"\".\nIt contains the following pieces:\n\"The Defenders of Aleroth were a group of wizards who at the height of the Great War formed a cabal that was to play a pivotal part in the city's defense. Experienced casters all, they were terrifying opponents who refused to yield when an army of Demons launched a massive assault. None of them survived, but the carnage they had inflicted was of such a scale that they have become legends among the people of Rivellon and today, sparse though its numbers may be, their equipment is sought after by even the most powerful of battle mages.\nMagic was the Defenders' first line of attack and defense, yes, but they knew too much about war not to encase themselves in the protection of steel. Wrought by the armour smiths that would later supply the Aleroth Champions, their armours are brilliant pieces of workmanship. It is no coincidence all but exact replicas of them are now fashioned for those who enlist in the ranks of the New Order of Rivertown.\" "}
{"id": "3965", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3965", "title": "Defenders of Aleroth Vampire Mace", "text": "\" is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Weapons%23One-Handed%20Warhammer\"&gt;special warhammer&lt;/a&gt; in '.\nDescription.\nDefenders of Aleroth Vampire Mace is a special mace that used to belong to a group of wizards that defended &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; during the Great War and is part of the &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Set\"&gt;Defenders of Aleroth Set&lt;/a&gt;. The set is constituted of &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Helmet\"&gt;helmet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Armour\"&gt;armour&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Leggings\"&gt;leggings&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Defenders%20of%20Aleroth%20Vampire%20Mace\"&gt;mace&lt;/a&gt;. It requires atleast level 14 in order to be equipped. When equipped the mace will boost &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; attribute by 4 points and Mana by 28 points. The weapon has 1 charm slot and 2 enchantments slot. The default enchantment is Butcher.\nHow to Obtain.\nRetrieved from the chest outside &lt;a href=\"Needleman%27s%20storage\"&gt;Needleman's storage&lt;/a&gt;. If &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley\"&gt;Broken Valley&lt;/a&gt; \"has not been destroyed yet\", this can be obtained by having &lt;a href=\"Sosostra\"&gt;Sosostra&lt;/a&gt; tell &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt;'s fortune three times then head to &lt;a href=\"Maxos%27%20Temple\"&gt;Maxos' Temple&lt;/a&gt;. On the path &lt;a href=\"Bellegar\"&gt;Bellegar&lt;/a&gt; will appear and teleport the Knight to the storage exterior. After the Valley has been destroyed, the chest cannot be obtained even though the storage is accessible.\nSet Properties.\nDefenders of Aleroth Vampire Mace is a part of the set Defenders of Aleroth Set which allows the item to gain additional, potentially increasing, properties the more items of the same set are worn. Defenders of Aleroth Vampire Mace primary increased attribute is Magic Damage, which is firstly gained by equipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping more items from the set. "}
{"id": "3564", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3564", "title": "Defensive Posture", "text": "Defensive Posture is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills%23Warrior\"&gt;Warrior skill&lt;/a&gt; that can be used by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nDefensive Posture is a active Warrior skill that allows the Knight to greatly boost their armour at the cost of their damage. This skill can be cast with any weapon in hand.\nNote: These values apply to your melee and ranged values like worn armor (with diminishing returns); they are not added directly to the resistance values.\u00a0The higher your base armor, the lower the final damage resistance increase will be when these values are added.\ne.g. With 18.16% damage resistance, +42 armor will yield 44.57% damage resistance; an 28.41% increase.\u00a0At 57.56% damage resistance, +42 armor will yield 65.97% damage resistance, an 8.41% increase.\nSomething to keep in mind with \"diminishing returns\" like these is that diminishing numbers doesn't necessarily mean diminishing effectiveness.\u00a0Given 1,000\u00a0hp (for easy numbers), 60% damage reduction means the player will take 40% of incoming damage, surviving a blow up to ~2,500.\u00a0Increasing that by 6% to the cap may not seem like much, but now the player will survive up to 2,940 damage... a 17% increase in damage necessary for a kill.\u00a0Likewise, a damage reduction increase from 71% to 75% (if the cap went that high) would be \"diminishing returns\" of only a 4% increase, but actually allows the player to survive 16% more damage taken.\u00a0Defensive Posture will always be useful and give roughly the same survivability bonus until it pushes your damage reduction past the cap of 66% (where more becomes useless).\nDefensive Posture be canceled at any time, the cooldown starts after the duration ends or after it is manually turned off.\nThe following are mutually exclusive, only one can be active at the same time: &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20the%20Battle%20Mage\"&gt;Way of the Battle Mage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20the%20Wise%20Wizard\"&gt;Way of the Wise Wizard&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20the%20Ranger\"&gt;Way of the Ranger&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Rage\"&gt;Battle Rage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Defensive%20Posture\"&gt;Defensive Posture&lt;/a&gt;."}
