{"id": "15247", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15247", "title": "Elrath", "text": " is a charlatan &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20characters\"&gt;doctor&lt;/a&gt; living in &lt;a href=\"Rivertown\"&gt;Rivertown&lt;/a&gt; in 1218 AD.\nBackground.\nAs the doctor tasked with curing the grey death afflicting the residents of the &lt;a href=\"poor%20area\"&gt;poor area&lt;/a&gt; in Rivertown, he is treated as a saviour by those under his care. In reality, he is a fake healer and is the actual cause of the plague: he poisoned the well out of spite towards the poor. However the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt; intended to use the poison to weaken the &lt;a href=\"Ducal%20Army\"&gt;Ducal Army&lt;/a&gt;, an order which Elrath seemingly ignored.\nThis reality is eventually discovered by &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; who breaks into Elrath's house in Rivertown's market. Upon discovering Lucian and realising the latter knows the false doctor's secret, Elrath sets about attempting to cover his tracks, sending &lt;a href=\"assassin\"&gt;assassin&lt;/a&gt;s to eliminate the hero. Ultimately this proves unsuccessful and the &lt;a href=\"Rivertown%20Watch\"&gt;Rivertown Watch&lt;/a&gt; is made aware of his actions."}
