{"id": "2243", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2243", "title": "Enchanter", "text": "An enchanter is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;person&lt;/a&gt; that can &lt;a href=\"enchantments\"&gt;enchant&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armour%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;armour&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Jewelry%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;jewelry&lt;/a&gt; with magical auras and buffs.\nEnchanters.\nThe following people are enchanters:\nEnchantment Information.\nYou must talk to your enchanter while you have the &lt;a href=\"Enchantments%2C%20Potions%20and%20Formulas\"&gt;formula&lt;/a&gt; you want them to learn. The formula then disappears from your inventory, and your enchanter learns that enchantment. (Example: I have Butcher 5 formula and talk to my enchanter. He learns Butcher 5. The Formula disappears.) If your enchanter already knows the spell, you will keep the formula in your inventory.\nList of Enchantments.\nNote: The values given refer to the original '. The enchantments were revised and generally improved for the ' / \"Developer's Cut\" releases of the game."}
{"id": "5005", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5005", "title": "Enchanter (Original Sin)", "text": "Enchanter is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%20Classes\"&gt;mage class&lt;/a&gt; in ' and the '.\nBackground.\n&lt;a href=\"Orc\"&gt;Orc&lt;/a&gt;s? Puppets. Creatures of the Void? Dolls. For the Enchanter, enemies are more toys than threats, and battle is equal play and experimentation.\nRaised by dedicated natural philosophers, the enchanter grew up believing the less-desirable races were profoundly important. A living orc could be experimented upon in ways one would never dream of applying to a &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;, after all.\nTrained to assist in capturing and controlling these test subjects, the enchanter's expertise is unparalleled. What those natural philosophers didn't expect, however, was for their well-trained enchanter to realise the horror of their experiments and to turn that expertise against them.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Source%20Hunters\"&gt;Source Hunters&lt;/a&gt; who pulled them down from the spikes upon which they'd been compelled to impale themselves offered the enchanter a choice: Rot in jail, or turn those powers of manipulation toward the greater good.\nStarting statistics.\nFollowing table shows all statistics, spells and items of the Enchanter at the start of the game. There are no major differences between Classic and Enhanced versions of the game save for few minor changes in skills, abilities and items at their disposal. \nIn \"Enhanced Edition\" their witchcraft skill &lt;a href=\"Enfeebling%20Touch\"&gt;Enfeebling Touch&lt;/a&gt; (from Classic Edition) got replaced with &lt;a href=\"Oath%20of%20Desecration\"&gt;Oath of Desecration&lt;/a&gt; witchcraft skill. Another difference is that instead of ability the Enchanter has now &lt;a href=\"Wand%20%28skill%29\"&gt;Wand&lt;/a&gt; ability. Following this change their original weapon &lt;a href=\"Source%20Hunter%27s%20Air%20Staff\"&gt;Source Hunter's Air Staff&lt;/a&gt; got replaced with &lt;a href=\"Old%20Wooden%20Water%20Wand\"&gt;Old Wooden Water Wand&lt;/a&gt;. In addition to this the Enchanters number of minor healing potions got reduced from 2 to 1 and their &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Ice%20Elemental\"&gt;Summon Ice Elemental scroll&lt;/a&gt; was replaced with &lt;a href=\"Blitz%20Bolt\"&gt;Blitz Bolt scroll&lt;/a&gt;. "}
{"id": "10588", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10588", "title": "Enchanter (Original Sin 2)", "text": "The Enchanter is a support &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;mage class&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nSummary.\nEnchanter is a mage who are focused on &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; magic in order to support their allies. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt; which they need in order to wield their chosen weapon, a two-handed staff. Their combat abilities are further boosted by their talent &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; which increases the range of their spells by 2 meters. \nThe Enchanters startings spells are &lt;a href=\"Electric%20Discharge\"&gt;Electric Discharge&lt;/a&gt; which in combination with their second starting spell &lt;a href=\"Rain\"&gt;Rain&lt;/a&gt; can deal great air damage and potentially stun their Wet enemies. Their third and last starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Restoration%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Restoration&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to heal their allies and damage undead enemies.\nCivil ability of the Enchanter is &lt;a href=\"Loremaster\"&gt;Loremaster&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to identify properties of found gear and the weaknesses of their enemies. \nOut of all companions &lt;a href=\"Lohse\"&gt;Lohse&lt;/a&gt; is the one who chooses this specialisation by default. \nMercenary Aurnia.\nAurnia is an &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Dwarves\"&gt;dwarven&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be &lt;a href=\"Companions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Recruiting%20Mercenaries\"&gt;hired&lt;/a&gt; from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. Her role on the battlefield is that of enchanter, a mage who manipulates air and water to support their allies.\nDetailed Description.\nList of all skills.\nEnchanter is a class focused on casting &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophy\"&gt;Hydrosophy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurgy\"&gt;Aerotheurgy&lt;/a&gt; spells. Both of these are capable of supporting their allies and dealing damage to their enemies. Hydrosophy is focused on powers of water that allow Cleric to restore Magic Armour, summon rain and freeze their opponents. Aerotheurgy allows Enchanter to teleport their allies and foes, increase their allies movement and stun their enemies by summoning lightning and storms.\nFollowing table shows all spells which Enchanter can learn as they level up and invest points in respective combat abilities."}
{"id": "3508", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3508", "title": "Enchantments", "text": ""}
{"id": "4386", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4386", "title": "Enchantments, Potions and Formulas", "text": "A formula is simply a recipe for an enchantment or potion. There is no specific dialog tree in which you offer formulas to an enchanter or alchemist. All you need do is speak to them while having a formula in your inventory. The formula will disappear and the NPC will learn the recipe. From then on it is available from their dialog menu.\nIt is important to note that if the NPC has already learned a formula, it will not be used, but will remain in your inventory. You can then sell or destroy the duplicate formula.\nExample: I have \"Butcher 5 Formula\" and talk to my enchanter. He learns Butcher 5. The Formula disappears. If the enchanter / alchemist already knows the recipe, I retain the formula in my inventory.\nFormulars carry over between different specialists that you meet.\nEnchantments of a similar type do not stack as the following example shows: I have already enchanted a pair of leggings with \"Increased Mana 2\", then I cannot add another Increased Mana spell to them.\nYou do, however, have the ability to Disenchant the item first, then enchant it with one of your choice. The type of enchantment you can use is linked to the item being enchanted (see tables below).\nThe number of ingredients you need depends on your platform level. A level 3 platform only needs 1x Fanny Blossom and 3x Ginseng for a healing 10 potion. But a level 1 platform needs 2x Fanny Blossom and 5x Ginseng to make one.\nFor potion formulas see: &lt;a href=\"Alchemist\"&gt;Alchemist&lt;/a&gt;\nFor additional enchantment formulas see: &lt;a href=\"Enchanter\"&gt;Enchanter&lt;/a&gt;"}
