{"id": "22846", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22846", "title": "Entropic Bite (Original Sin 2)", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;tierless Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; released as part of in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; skill that allows caster to bite their chosen target in 4 meter range from them. The bite will deal physical damage.\nCharacters without Physical will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Atrophy%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Atrophy&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 1 turn which will disarm them and thus prevent them from using weapon-based skills.\nSkillbook and Scroll.\n is a tierless skill that has no scroll or skillbook from which it can be learnt or cast. \nThis skill is exclusive to the &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Hungry%20Flower\"&gt;Hungry Flower&lt;/a&gt; as it acquires this skill when it is under the effect of &lt;a href=\"Power%20Infusion\"&gt;Power Infusion&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; skill.\nModifiers.\n scales with &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, Level and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "10900", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10900", "title": "Environmental Effects (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Fire Surfaces.\nSources\nFire surfaces are one of the most common surfaces you'll encounter throughout your playthrough; they are also one of the most dangerous as they can spread quickly and if combined with poison or oil, they will explode for a great deal of damage. Walking through fire will set Burning on you, but it can be blocked by magic armor.\nThey can be doused using a water spell like Rain, air Frost, or spells like Battle Stomp which removes surfaces.\nCursed fire (Hellfire) does a lot more damage and is impossible to douse. While Blessed fire will turn blue and cure characters instead of damaging them.\nPoison Surfaces.\nSources\nPoison surfaces are another common one you'll encounter and they are just as deadly as fire. As stated above if combined with fire poison will explode. Walking through a poison field will set Poisoned on you, however it heals undead characters so keep that in mind.\nPoison surfaces can also be removed by things like Battle Stomp or replacing the field with water, oil or frost.\nFrozen Surfaces.\nSources\nFrozen surfaces do not set any statuses upon players, but being on a frozen surface will give you a chance to be Knocked Down if you move on them. Crafting nails to your boots will grant them Slipping immunity.\nFrozen surfaces can be melted with fire.\nCursed frost will eventually freeze you as you walk over it, bypassing the Magic armor.\nWet Surfaces.\nSources\nWet surfaces don't cause any problems directly, but they can be electrocuted and create a large stunning pool that will be incredibly difficult to escape from without something to destroy or replace the surface with.\nWet surfaces can be used as a protection against spreading fires. Water and fire creates vapor and a dry ground.\nBlood Surfaces.\nSources\nBlood surfaces act much like Wet ones with the exception of the talent Leech that interacts with blood. They can also be electrocuted like wet surfaces and replaced/destroyed in the same manner."}
{"id": "20224", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20224", "title": "Enwebbed (Status)", "text": "Enwebbed or Web is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nEnwebbed is a negative environmental &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; which incapacitates all characters that come into contact with \"web surface\" and do not have immunity to it. Due to its incapacitating properties Enwebbed causes Movement Speed - 100 % and Dodging - 70 %. Additionally afflicted character cannot be targeted by teleportation skills and spells.\nCause.\nEnwebbed is only caused if character without Immunity to Enwebbed comes into contact with web surface. Web surface can be found in few places on &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; or created through the skill &lt;a href=\"Spin%20Web\"&gt;Spin Web&lt;/a&gt; which is gained by casting &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Legs\"&gt;Spider Legs&lt;/a&gt; spell. \"Web surface\" on its own, has only set chance to cause Enwebbed. However \"cursed web\" will always apply Enwebbed status.\nTreatment.\nEnwebbed can be cancelled only by the following ways. &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; spell Spider Legs provide immunity to Enwebbed status. &lt;a href=\"Bless%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Blessing&lt;/a&gt; the web will turn it into blessed web which provides &lt;a href=\"Hasted%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Hasted&lt;/a&gt; status instead of Enwebbed. One way to cancel out Enwebbed is also by setting afflicted character on Fire (&lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Fire%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Holy Fire&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Necrofire%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Necrofire&lt;/a&gt;). \nUnlike most negative status effects, Enwebbed will always ignore armour values."}
{"id": "10430", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10430", "title": "Epidemic of Fire", "text": "Epidemic of Fire is an &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;expert pyrokinetic source skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive pyrokinetic source skill that allows character to hurl a cursed stream of fire at their target. The stream of fire does not stop at the first target but will split and jump to other enemies in at least 10 meter range from the target up to five times. The deals fire damage (note that the stream will not damage the same target twice) and creates a cursed fire surface upon making contact with target(s). Cursed fire surface will last indefinitely. Due to its nature, any flammable surfaces and clouds (oil, poison and web) will be set on fire and transformed into fire surface. \nCharacters without Magic Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Necrofire%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Necrofire&lt;/a&gt; status and suffer damage directly to their health.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinesis\"&gt;Pyrokinesis&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill is reflected back when the target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill (Definitive Edition only).\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 2 free memory slots. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 750 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Fire%20Skillbook\"&gt;High Tier Blank Fire Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a expert Pyrokinetic skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 13.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 350 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves varies. The cost to cast the as a source skill is 3 Action Points and 2 &lt;a href=\"Source%20Points%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Source Points&lt;/a&gt;. The cost to cast scroll is only 2 Action Points.\nBoth the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills, attributes and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have level and then Pyrokinetic ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Intelligence provides the lowest bonus out of the three (3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Pyrokinetic).\nWhen it comes to enemies they may resist fire damage if they have: Fire Immunity Status and high enough Fire Resistance (which lowers fire damage done).\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills. \nLocation.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell pyrokinetic spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met."}
{"id": "12397", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12397", "title": "Equalise", "text": "Equalise is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;master Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nVitality and Armour percentages of characters in target area are summed up and redistributed equally.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Metamorphosis\"&gt;Metamorphosis&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 1400 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Polymorph%20Skillbook\"&gt;High Tier Blank Polymorph Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a master Polymorph skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 16.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 350 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell Polymorph spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. "}
{"id": "17051", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17051", "title": "Eraser Grenade", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Gift%20Bag%20-%20Song%20Of%20Nature\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \"\"\nCharacteristics.\n is a throwable grenade that deals no damage but instead clears out any surfaces and clouds in an area of impact (3 meter radius). This includes also special surfaces such as Deathfog, lava and &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;. \nAll characters can throw this grenade. However due to the grenade dealing no damage and only clearing out surfaces and clouds it is not possible to increase its effectiveness through abilities or attributes.\nSince is a grenade it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Ambidextrous&lt;/a&gt; talent which decreases the cost of using grenades and scrolls by 1 AP when the secondary hand is free. is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Slingshot&lt;/a&gt; which increases its range by 5 meters and by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent which increases range by 2 meters."}
