{"id": "4178", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4178", "title": "Erlking", "text": " is a goblin servant of &lt;a href=\"Laiken\"&gt;Laiken&lt;/a&gt; residing in &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Tower\"&gt;Battle Tower&lt;/a&gt; in 1300 AD.\nBackground.\nErlking is a goblin who was present for &lt;a href=\"Laiken\"&gt;Laiken&lt;/a&gt; 's &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Forge\"&gt;Soul Forge&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Laiken\"&gt;Laiken&lt;/a&gt; cut out his vocal cords so that Erlking could not tell anyone the name of the Demon &lt;a href=\"Laiken\"&gt;Laiken&lt;/a&gt; was forged with. He regards the Knight indifferently and does not make any hostile moves towards the Knight, even if the Knight points on his lack of tongue. However he will refuse to write the name even if asked."}
{"id": "19658", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19658", "title": "Erlking's Writings", "text": "Erlking's Writings is a special &lt;a href=\"Stats%20Book\"&gt;Stats Book&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". \nDescription.\nThis book was written by &lt;a href=\"Erlking\"&gt;Erlking&lt;/a&gt; and gives two stat points when read.\nLocation.\nIts location can be acquired by &lt;a href=\"Mindread\"&gt;Mindread&lt;/a&gt;ing the resurrected &lt;a href=\"Sassan\"&gt;Sassan&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"What%27s%20in%20a%20Name\"&gt;What's in a Name&lt;/a&gt;. It will then be located on a large table near the entrance of Erlking's room on the 1st floor library in the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Tower\"&gt;Battle Tower&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "5933", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5933", "title": "Eroding Strike", "text": "Description.\nWeaken your target. Does 30% weapon damage. \n100% base chance to set \nNotes.\nThe Eroding Strike skill book is only sold by the unlockable Fire element merchant in Homestead. Another copy can be obtained as one of three rewards that can be chosen after solving a certain puzzle dungeon, exclusive to &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20Spray\"&gt;Arrow Spray&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt;. As of version 1.0.107.0, the Eroding Strike skill book has been sold by Hiver, the warrior skill book vendor in the Silverglen tavern (characters were at level 13). As of version 1.0.219.0, the skill book has been sold by &lt;a href=\"Ellary\"&gt;Ellary&lt;/a&gt;, the women vendor in the Silerglen tavern (characters at level 13)."}
{"id": "12284", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12284", "title": "Erratic Wisp", "text": "Erratic wisp is a &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; skill in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nErratic wisp causes target character to teleport in a random direction each time they are damaged with physical attack from weapons. Increases Air Resistance by 40%. \nThis skill does not prevent from being damaged. If person under its effect avoids damage by dodging, teleportation is not triggered.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into both &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Aerotheurge\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 190 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a any non-source &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Aerotheurge\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks are combined. Since is a mixed skill, traders do not have the skillbook for sale.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nLocation.\nTraders.\nThis skill cannot be bought or stolen from NPCs in the game. "}
{"id": "17669", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17669", "title": "Escape from Fort Joy", "text": "Fort Joy (renamed in the Definitive Edition) is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;main quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". It is started at the beginning of Act II.\nQuick walkthrough.\nThis quest may be completed in several ways:\nDetailed walkthrough.\nFollowing the wreckage in Act I, the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; find him/herself alive on the shore of &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy%20Beach\"&gt;Fort Joy beach&lt;/a&gt; and his/her first objective becomes to find a way to escape from Fort Joy.\nEntering Fort Joy.\nGoing south, he/she eventually enter in &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy%20ghetto\"&gt;Fort Joy ghetto&lt;/a&gt;; from there, a way should be found for sneaking into the Fort Joy proper, which is possible in several ways.\nFinding Someone who knows a Way Out of the Fort.\nThe most intuitive way to access the fort is following one of the related quests available at the ghetto. In particular, the following ways will eventually lead to the &lt;a href=\"Holding%20cells\"&gt;Holding Cells&lt;/a&gt; beneath the Fort:\nIndependently of the way followed to reach the Holding Cells, the only way out is to retrieve the &lt;a href=\"Keys%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Prison Key&lt;/a&gt; from the group of Magisters on the east part of the area to open the door at north. Using the key will give access to the ground floor of Fort Joy.\nUsing the Force.\nIf your party is strong enough, you may also directly attack &lt;a href=\"Borris\"&gt;Magister Borris&lt;/a&gt; and his comrades near the main gate of Fort Joy. One of them drops the key that opens the gate. Once inside, you may explore the outside area or going through the main door which give access to the ground floor (where you arrive passing by the Holding Cells).\nSneaking in the Fort by Yourself.\nOnce the &lt;a href=\"Gloves%20of%20Teleportation\"&gt;Gloves of Teleportation&lt;/a&gt; are retrieved during the quest The Teleporter, they could be used to teleport a party member to the ledge behind Mona's tent and have him/her to drop down the ladder to help the rest of the party to climb up. From there, the Godwoken may enter the Orivand's Chambers (it does require Lockpicking or the key given by &lt;a href=\"Yarrow\"&gt;Magister Yarrow&lt;/a&gt; at the end of &lt;a href=\"The%20Murderous%20Gheist\"&gt;The Murderous Gheist&lt;/a&gt;) or may sneak behind the guards at the front gate and entering the fort proper.\nLeaving Fort Joy.\nOnce entered the Fort, again there are several ways to escape from it:\nAfter leaving the fort, the character is awarded with experience and a new quest is acquired.\nNote: Independently of the way used to leave Fort Joy, it is suggested to go back and explore all the remaining areas for loot and experience"}
