{"id": "10862", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10862", "title": "Ferol", "text": "Ferol is a duchy prominently featured in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\" and mentioned in ' and '.\nBackground.\n\"Divine Divinity\".\nMost of \"Divine Divinity\" takes place in the duchy of Ferol and its Duke, &lt;a href=\"Janus%20Ferol\"&gt;Janus Ferol&lt;/a&gt;, is a major character in the game. It's unclear how far its borders extend; parts of the Dark Forest don't seem to be entirely part of Ferol, and it's unclear whether or not &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; is within the duchy. The Farmlands seem to be within its borders, however, and Verdistis is either within Ferol or directly bordering it.\n\"Divinity II: Ego Draconis\".\nThe duchy is referenced by some of the literature in \"Ego Draconis\", and was the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt;'s homeland according to flavor text. While the Dragon Knight can't enter Ferol proper (unless Aleroth is a part of the duchy) they can visit the path to it, but will be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Kali%27s%20Flying%20Fortress\"&gt;Kali's Flying Fortress&lt;/a&gt;. \n\"Divinity: Original Sin\".\nAlthough Ferol itself isn't featured in the game, the current Duke of Ferol makes an appearance in &lt;a href=\"Cyseal\"&gt;Cyseal&lt;/a&gt; and, according to legend, Cyseal itself was founded by two former citizens of Ferol."}
{"id": "13533", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13533", "title": "Ferris", "text": "Ferris is a member of the &lt;a href=\"Ducal%20Army\"&gt;Ducal Army&lt;/a&gt; found guarding the bridge to &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"the%20Farmlands\"&gt;the Farmlands&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nFerris is a member of the contingent lead by &lt;a href=\"Seth\"&gt;Seth&lt;/a&gt; to travel to Aleroth in order to seek the healer's aid in dealing with the plague in &lt;a href=\"Rivertown\"&gt;Rivertown&lt;/a&gt;. Upon reaching the bridge, both he and &lt;a href=\"Jupiter\"&gt;Jupiter&lt;/a&gt; volunteered to remain behind to guard the bridge after the &lt;a href=\"orc\"&gt;orc&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"troll\"&gt;troll&lt;/a&gt; attacks from beyond were identified."}
{"id": "4997", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4997", "title": "Fighter (Original Sin)", "text": "Fighter is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%20Classes\"&gt;warrior class&lt;/a&gt; in ' and the '.\nBackground.\nThere was no &lt;a href=\"Legion\"&gt;Legion&lt;/a&gt; in the slums of &lt;a href=\"Yuthul%20Gor\"&gt;Yuthul Gor&lt;/a&gt;. There was no mayor, no magistrate, no law. Only the fighter. If your horse had been stolen, the fighter would find it. If your landlord extorted you, the fighter would help him see reason. This justice was harsh but effective; order persisted.\nWhen the king heard of the vigilante who dared enforce the law without the monarch's consent, he was outraged. 'Banish this traitor,' the king said. But the king's guards could not subdue the warrior, no matter their swords and spears.\nAt last, the king called upon a black witch to cast a spell upon the so-called usurper. As the fighter slept, terrible nightmares invaded where soldiers could not. Mad with terror, the fighter fled and wandered for weeks before the nightmares began to subside, but if the fighter dared wander in the direction of home, the nightmares began afresh.\nThe king might be untouchable, but dark magic was not. As a &lt;a href=\"Source%20Hunter\"&gt;Source Hunter&lt;/a&gt;, the fighter would destroy the charm at its root. The king would come after.\nStarting statistics.\nFollowing table shows all statistics, spells and items of the Fighter at the start of the game. There are no major differences between Classic and Enhanced versions of the game save for few minor changes in skills and items at their disposal. \nIn \"Classic Edition\" the Fighter used to have &lt;a href=\"Dust%20Devil\"&gt;Dust Devil&lt;/a&gt; skill as their default skill, which had been replaced with &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20Fist%20%28DOS%20EE%29\"&gt;Crushing Fist&lt;/a&gt; skill. Another difference is that in \"Classic Edition\" the Fighter has 2 &lt;a href=\"Healing%20Potion%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;minor healing potions&lt;/a&gt; at their disposal, whereas in Enhanced Edition Fighter has only 1 potion. In addition to this, Fighter in \"Enhanced Edition\" has &lt;a href=\"Firestorm%20Grenade\"&gt;Firestorm Grenade&lt;/a&gt; in their inventory."}
{"id": "10589", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10589", "title": "Fighter (Original Sin 2)", "text": "The Fighter is a &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;warrior class&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nSummary.\nFighters are warriors who alongside their &lt;a href=\"Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; skill rely on the &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; magic to bolster their physical defenses. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;. Their weapon of choice are one handed swords, axes or maces with a shield.\nThe Fighters first starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Stomp\"&gt;Battle Stomp&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to knock down enemies in front of them and clear of some surfaces such as ice and fire. The second starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Bouncing%20Shield\"&gt;Bouncing Shield&lt;/a&gt; which lets them throw their shield at an enemy and if there is another enemy in 5 meter range they will be struck as well. The third and final skill is &lt;a href=\"Fortify\"&gt;Fortify&lt;/a&gt; which allows the Fighter to boost their physical armour. In combat the Fighter may also rely on their talent &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Opportunist&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to attack any enemies that move next to them. \nOutside combat they rely on their &lt;a href=\"Bartering%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Bartering&lt;/a&gt; civil skill to haggle better prices when trading. \nOut of all companions &lt;a href=\"The%20Red%20Prince\"&gt;The Red Prince&lt;/a&gt; is the one who chooses this specialisation by default.\nMercenary Nestor.\nNestor is a &lt;a href=\"Dwarves\"&gt;dwarven&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be &lt;a href=\"Companions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Recruiting%20Mercenaries\"&gt;hired&lt;/a&gt; from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. His role on the battlefield is that of fighter, a warrior who alongside his &lt;a href=\"Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; skills relies on &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; magic to vanquish his foes.\nDetailed description.\nList of all skills available.\nFighter is a class focused on casting &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; skills and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; spells. Following table shows all skills and spells which Fighter can learn as they level up and invest points in respective combat abilities."}
