{"id": "14905", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14905", "title": "Find the Teleporter Activation Scrolls", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\" obtained on meeting &lt;a href=\"Zandalor\"&gt;Zandalor&lt;/a&gt;.\nWalkthrough.\nOn meeting Zandalor he will mention the teleporters around &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; that have been left inactive to prevent misuse. In order to activate them, Lucian needs to find the remaining six &lt;a href=\"teleporter%20activation%20scroll\"&gt;teleporter activation scroll&lt;/a&gt;s. Zandalor gives Lucian the wizard scroll, but to find another scrolls, Zandalor suggests to searching cursed abbey nearby for the human scroll and to ask the Elven lord Elredor, who can be found around Archers Guild, for the elven scroll.\nThe human scroll can be obtain from either the cursed abbey, or from &lt;a href=\"Mitox\"&gt;Mitox&lt;/a&gt;.\nHead along the paths south after crossing the bridge to &lt;a href=\"The%20Farmlands\"&gt;The Farmlands&lt;/a&gt; to the Archer's Guild's outpost to meet Elredor, who hands over the scroll without much discussion after being asked to do so by Zandalor in a dream.\nBefore Goemoe is captured by the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt;, he denies knowledge of the scroll, even though he holds it. After he has been rescued from the Black Ring, he will hand it over willingly.\nOne can be found on the table in &lt;a href=\"Krasnegar\"&gt;Krasnegar's&lt;/a&gt; room in the Dwarven Bread Inn. Another is lying on a table in the mayor's house in the dwarven village, Glenborous. You can also receive one as a reward for completing a quest for the dwarven king in the Dwarven Halls.\nIt can be found in a chest in Baluk's tent in the Orc Camp. Baluk holds the key to the chest."}
