{"id": "10942", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10942", "title": "Invisibility Potion (Original Sin 2)", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Consumables%23Potions\"&gt;potion&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a potion that can be used by a character in order to grant them &lt;a href=\"Invisible%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Invisible&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 5 turns. It is the smallest variety of the potion and it is also the only type of the potion that can be crafted. It is not affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; and its base value is 200 gold.\nMedium Invisibility Potion is a potion that can be used by a character in order to grant them &lt;a href=\"Invisible%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Invisible&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 10 turns. It is stronger than the base invisibility potion but it cannot be crafted. It is not affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; and its base value is 350 gold.\nLarge Invisibility Potion is a potion that can be used by a character in order to grant them &lt;a href=\"Invisible%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Invisible&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 15 turns. It is the strongest type of invisibility potion but like its medium-sized counterpart cannot be crafted. It is not affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; and its base value is 1000 gold.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of potions and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for. "}
