{"id": "13060", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13060", "title": "Janus Ferol", "text": " is the 12-year-old duke of &lt;a href=\"Ferol\"&gt;Ferol&lt;/a&gt; and the antagonist of \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBackground.\nAfter his father's death, ostensibly of a heart attack, Janus Ferol became the duke of Ferol despite being only 12 years old. According to some of his subjects, his rule had been surprisingly stable despite his age, mostly credited to his advisor.\nSome time before the start of \"Divine Divinity\", he began declaring himself the Divine One, and recruits a local Hero as his Lord Protector. During their time as Lord Protector, Janus has the Hero carry out meaningless tasks, like finding his &lt;a href=\"Arhu\"&gt;cat&lt;/a&gt; and delivering letters to his concubine &lt;a href=\"Lela\"&gt;Lela&lt;/a&gt;. He only calls upon them for real work during a meeting with several aristocrats and merchants, apparently to reinforce his status is Divine One. After being attacked by Orc assassins during the meeting, Janus has the Hero thrown out of Stormfist Castle.\nOver the course of the game, &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Zandalor\"&gt;Zandalor&lt;/a&gt; discover that Janus had his father assassinated. When he was younger, Janus touched the Sword of Lies, a vessel made to imprison the Demon of Lies. This released the demon, who destroyed Janus' soul and engineered his rise to power to spread chaos. After a ritual to turn the Hero into the actual Divine One, Janus arrives at the Council of Seven and kills all but two of them, revealing his true demonic form to the few survivors.\nThe Hero arrives back in Rivellon two months later, while the Demon of Lies (who has dropped his Janus disguise entirely) is preparing to resurrect his god, the Chaos Demon, through a human baby. The Hero, now the Divine One, fights his way through the Demon's forces and kills him, although too late to prevent the baby from becoming the &lt;a href=\"Damian\"&gt;Chaos God's vessel&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "17389", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17389", "title": "Jar of Honey", "text": "The is a type of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Consumables%23Food%20and%20Drink\"&gt;food&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a consumable item which when consumed will restore 20 % of maximum Vitality, grant + 2 bonus points to &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; as well as increase Poison Resistance by + 15 %. Characters with &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; are healed for 40 % of maximum Vitality, gain + 4 bonus points to &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; as well as increased Poison Resistance by + 30 %. The effect of lasts 6 turns. \nPoisoned is a consumable item that was poisoned through various means (either &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Bottle%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;poison bottle&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Zaikk%27s%20Talon\"&gt;Zaikk's Talon&lt;/a&gt;). Poisoning the will reduce its value to 0. Instead of healing it will deal poison damage equal to 15 % of the consumers maximum Vitality, rendering it unsafe for the living but safe for &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; and grant + 2 bonus points to &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; as well as increased Poison Resistance by + 15 %. The effects last 6 turns.\nIf character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; the will deal poison damage equal to 40 % of the consumers maximum Vitality and grant + 4 bonus points to &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; as well as increased Poison Resistance by + 30 %. The effects last 6 turns. \nNote that poisoned item may be used in crafting, however the end product will be un-poisoned item.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for. "}
