{"id": "3197", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3197", "title": "Jewellery in Law", "text": "Jewellery in Law is a &lt;a href=\"Flames%20of%20Vengeance%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; received from &lt;a href=\"Ransid\"&gt;Ransid&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Lanilor%20Lane\"&gt;Lanilor Lane&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; during the events of \"\". \nDetailed Walkthrough.\nRansid says that he is poor and hungry, and would like you to retrieve &lt;a href=\"Mara%27s%20Earrings\"&gt;Mara's Earrings&lt;/a&gt; from his mother-in-law so that he can buy bread.\nHead east to the &lt;a href=\"Playhouse\"&gt;Playhouse&lt;/a&gt; and enter through the front door. Go down the hall, and turn right to the main (stage) area. You'll witness a cutscene and see the &lt;a href=\"ghost\"&gt;ghost&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Alfred\"&gt;Alfred&lt;/a&gt; leave the area. Get the key on the table in the northeast corner of the room, and open the backstage door in the southwest. Follow the hall, passing an inaccessible room (due a magical barrier), and speak with Alfred to obtain the quest &lt;a href=\"All%20the%20After%20World%27s%20a%20Stage\"&gt;All the After World's a Stage&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter completing that quest the magical barrier is lifted. This allows you to enter the room and speak to the ghost of Ransid's mother-in-law, Mara (she is not the same &lt;a href=\"Mara\"&gt;Mara&lt;/a&gt; you may have met at the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Boar\"&gt;Black Boar Inn&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley\"&gt;Broken Valley&lt;/a&gt;). Speak to her about Ransid, and she'll hesitantly give you the earrings, hoping that he uses the gold from their sale to drink too much and die choking on his own vomit.\nReturn to Ransid to give him the &lt;a href=\"jewelry\"&gt;jewelry&lt;/a&gt;. He's happy now that he \"\"can go to &lt;a href=\"Madame%20Eve%27s\"&gt;Madame Eve's&lt;/a&gt;! And ... buy bread, of course!\"\""}
