{"id": "20257", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20257", "title": "Knocked Down (Status)", "text": "Knocked Down is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nKnocked Down is a negative environmental and skill status effect. Characters afflicted by it will become incapacitated and unable to act. The effect takes place only if character does not have Physical armour above 0. The only exception to this rule are characters with &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Glass Cannon&lt;/a&gt; talent and characters stepping unto \"frozen water surface\" and \"frozen blood surface\". Characters only have a chance to obtain Knocked Down status effect from these surfaces but it will ignore Physical armour.\nCause.\nKnocked Down can be caused by both surface and skills. On &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; it is the contact with \"frozen water surface\" and \"frozen blood surface\". Other means of afflicting Knocked Down involve skills from &lt;a href=\"Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; school or the usage of items.\nTreatment.\nAs with any other negative status effect, there are two ways how to avoid and negate its effects. First its important to keep Physical armour value above 0. Secondly status effect &lt;a href=\"Rested%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Rested&lt;/a&gt; protect from being affected by Knocked Down. Immunity to slipping will provide resistance towards Knocked Down afflicted by stepping on \"frozen water surface\" and \"frozen blood surface\".\nPhysical armour restoration.\nKnocked Down can be resisted if character has Physical armour above 0. This does not apply to characters with &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Glass Cannon&lt;/a&gt; talent.\nStatus removal.\nFollowing spells and skills will remove Knocked Down status entirely."}
