{"id": "3956", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3956", "title": "Layla, Wallace, Zachary, Sloan", "text": "Layla, Wallace, Zachary, and Sloan are four Bandits in the &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Camp\"&gt;Bandit Camp&lt;/a&gt; arguing over five stolen weapons. If you attempt to take one of the stolen weapons Layla will confront you. If you choose to keep the weapon the four bandits will attack, if not the weapon will be returned to the table.\nWhen the bandits attack, if you are able to stand a few hits stay still and take the rest of the weapons as well. If you kill them and then return the table and weapons will be gone."}
{"id": "10729", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10729", "title": "Leadership", "text": "Leadership is a &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;combat skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nLeadership is a skill that grants allies around the character that possess the points invested into leadership a bonus to resistances and dodging around the 8 meter radius of the character with said skill. However the character that possesses the leadership skill does not acquire these bonuses. "}
{"id": "10161", "revid": "53818033", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10161", "title": "Leadership (DOS EE)", "text": "General.\nThe Leadership skill is extremely useful for one person on your team to invest in. When your teammates have direct line of sight to the character with Leadership, it provides massive offensive and defensive boosts, even making them immune to . It is most effective on a character, as they will always be in view in the middle of the fight, though it will work on any character.\nScaling.\nNotes: * +2 Willpower only available to characters with Obedient and an ally with 5+ leadership. Characters with Obedient do not gain the level 6 Leadership bonuses and instead only gain the +2 Willpower. Obedient is best on casters as wands have no chance to miss and spells do not critically hit."}
{"id": "18827", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18827", "title": "League of the Damned", "text": ""}
{"id": "7142", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7142", "title": "Leandra", "text": "Leandra, also known as the Conduit, is the leader of &lt;a href=\"Immaculates\"&gt;the Immaculates&lt;/a&gt; in 4 AR.\nBackground.\n&lt;a href=\"Soul%20Forge\"&gt;Soul Forge&lt;/a&gt;d to her sister &lt;a href=\"Icara\"&gt;Icara&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0(also known as the White Witch)\u00a0as a child after witnessing their parents' murder. The sisters lived a solitary life in &lt;a href=\"Luculla%20Forest\"&gt;Luculla forest&lt;/a&gt;, caring for the animals and seldomly interacting with other &lt;a href=\"humans\"&gt;humans&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe arrival of the &lt;a href=\"Wizards\"&gt;wizard&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Zandalor\"&gt;Zandalor&lt;/a&gt; marked a dramatic change in the girls' lives, his kind nature had an immediate effect on Leandra and Icara. Being soulforged, the sisters were painfully aware of each other's romantic feelings for the wizard and when Zandalor and Icara declared thier love to Leandra she fled their home, heartbroken.\nIn her time of weakness, she was approached by &lt;a href=\"Trife\"&gt;Trife&lt;/a&gt; and seduced by the notion of the peaceful non-existence for all, offered by the &lt;a href=\"Void%20Dragon\"&gt;Void Dragon&lt;/a&gt;; to this end &lt;a href=\"Astarte\"&gt;Astarte&lt;/a&gt; would need to be sealed in &lt;a href=\"the%20Godbox\"&gt;the Godbox&lt;/a&gt;, replacing the dragon. It is then that Leandra takes on the guise of the Conduit. With the sisters' soulforge mangled, Leandra quickly spirals downward, leaving destruction and slaughter in her wake.\nIn pursuit of her goals, Leandra enters a deal with &lt;a href=\"Boreas\"&gt;King Boreas&lt;/a&gt;, providing him with an elemental staff capable of imprisoning his brothers, in exchange for his &lt;a href=\"Star%20Stone\"&gt;Star Stone&lt;/a&gt;, the lives of his &lt;a href=\"imp\"&gt;imp&lt;/a&gt; workers to act as fuel for more Blood Stones and the incarceration of her sister Icara.\nTo further her objective, the town of &lt;a href=\"Hunter%27s%20Edge\"&gt;Hunter's Edge&lt;/a&gt; was ransacked by &lt;a href=\"orcs\"&gt;orcs&lt;/a&gt; and tribesmen at Leandra's behest, the inhabitants sacrificed for additional Blood Stones. Although most everyone was cut down in order to create more Blood Stones, the &lt;a href=\"Source%20Hunter\"&gt;Source Hunter&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Madora\"&gt;Madora&lt;/a&gt; managed to make her way to Cyseal and Zandalor's home was left untouched due to his protective magics. Several of the villagers are reanimated and forced to work in a &lt;a href=\"tenebrium\"&gt;tenebrium&lt;/a&gt; mine, gathering the toxic ore used to construct Leandra's &lt;a href=\"Death%20Knight%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Death Knight&lt;/a&gt;s.\nAs &lt;a href=\"Scarlett%20and%20Roderick\"&gt;Scarlett and Roderick&lt;/a&gt; come to their final confrontation they were given the opportunity to repair Leandra's Soul Forge with Icara. \nInteractions with Player character.\nChoose to leave the sisters soul forge broken will result in having to face Leandra during the final battle with the Void Dragon. She summons Death Knights, and has two unique Death Knights known as &lt;a href=\"Death%20Prince\"&gt;Death Prince&lt;/a&gt;s, who guard her.\nIf the Soul Forge is restored, Leandra will come to her senses and trembles thinking about what she had done and will leave the area with Zandalor and Icara."}
