{"id": "3629", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3629", "title": "Life Leech (Dragon Knight Saga)", "text": "Life Leech is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills%23Warrior\"&gt;Warrior skill&lt;/a&gt; that can be used by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nLife Leech is a passive Warrior skill that allows the Knight to steal life-force of their enemies upon hitting them with melee attacks. This skill can be cast only with melee weapon in hand or free hands. Due to its nature, once learnt, it will be always active. \nThe skill will not work with ranged or magic attacks, this includes magic damage on weapons.\u00a0The blue numbers in parentheses on the character sheet will not apply to the life leach amount. Note that life Leech enchantment works only on melee attacks, not skills that utilise melee attack.\nThe Life Leech skill can effect multiple enemies in a single hit but it attempts to leech each enemy separately.\u00a0 At level 13 there is an ~1/3 chance to leech from one enemy with a single attack, ~1/9 to leech from two (1/3 * 1/3 = 1/9), a ~1/27 to leech from three enemies, etc. Simple example: At skill level 13, there is a 34% chance that a hit for 100 physical melee damage will heal the player for 32 life.\u00a0 "}
