{"id": "18519", "revid": "37013771", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18519", "title": "Titus (Flames of Vengeance)", "text": "Captain is a character in \"\".\nBackground.\nCaptain Titus was a &lt;a href=\"Champions%20of%20Aleroth\"&gt;Champion of Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; and commander of a &lt;a href=\"Zeppelin\"&gt;Zeppelin&lt;/a&gt; in 1300 AD when &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; came under siege by the flying fortresses of the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt;. The wizard &lt;a href=\"Zandalor%20the%20Wise\"&gt;Zandalor&lt;/a&gt;, with the aid of &lt;a href=\"Deodatus\"&gt;Deodatus&lt;/a&gt; and several other mages, erected a magical dome across the entire city, shielding it from the fortress' bombardments.\nWhen the &lt;a href=\"The%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;last Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; retrieved a magical artifact after traveling to the &lt;a href=\"Antediluvian%20Vault\"&gt;Antediluvian Vault&lt;/a&gt;, Zandalor burst the shield, emitting a blast of magic that knocked the Black Ring's fortresses out of the sky.\nZandalor had devised a plan; a Zeppelin, escorted by the Dragon Knight and other zeppelins from Aleroth's fleet, would carry the magical artifact to the heart of the Black Ring's fortress-fleet, where it was believed &lt;a href=\"Damian\"&gt;Damian&lt;/a&gt; was commanding from, and use the artifact's power to obliterate it. Captain Titus' zeppelin was chosen to carry the artifact, and as soon as the barrier fell the Champions launched their fleet.\nThe battle was fierce, many zeppelins falling so that Titus' zeppelin could survive the approach. Titus provided fire support, shelling any targets designated by the Dragon Knight. Zandalor revealed that he could not sense Damian in the fortress, but rather &lt;a href=\"Ygerna\"&gt;Ygerna&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Behrlihn\"&gt;Behrlihn&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpon the final approach, Titus' zeppelin had received significant damage, to the point that Titus believed they would not be able to make the return trip to Aleroth. Whilst being bombarded by countless ballistae and beset upon by aerial foes from all directions, Titus steered his zeppelin into the fortress' main structure and activated the artifact. His sacrifice destroyed the Flying Fortress, killing Ygerna and winning the battle."}
