{"id": "9754", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9754", "title": "Tornado (DOS EE)", "text": ""}
{"id": "12275", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12275", "title": "Tornado (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Tornado is a &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;master Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive aerotheurge skill that allows caster to conjure a tornado which will randomly move in the direction of the caster's choice up to 13 meters from them. The tornado will clear all surfaces and clouds in its path. This includes lava, source and deathfog. All characters, including allies, who are in its path will have the following status effects removed: &lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Slowed%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Slowed&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Invisible%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Invisible&lt;/a&gt;.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurgy\"&gt;Aerotheurgy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if character is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Aerotheurge\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 1400 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Air%20Skillbook\"&gt;High Tier Blank Air Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a master Aerotheurge skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once player character or their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; reach level 16.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 260 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a supportive aerotheurge skill that allows caster to remove status effects and surfaces as well as clouds. Therefore it is not affected by the Level, Aerotheurge ability and &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; attribute of the caster.\nHowever the skill itself can still be affected by other skills and talents.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell hydrosophist spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met. Also note that &lt;a href=\"Lizard%20Dreamer\"&gt;Lizard Dreamer&lt;/a&gt; requires a persuasion check to be passed in order to speak with him, otherwise he (and the whole encampment) will turn hostile. "}
{"id": "22867", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22867", "title": "Torturer (Original Sin 2)", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;talent&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\n is an offensive talent that can be picked up by a character during character creation and has no level or combat ability requirement. It is not by default used by any of the preset classes. This talent allows character to apply 8 different harmful status effects to other characters regardless of their Physical and Magic Armour values as well as extend their duration by one turn. The method through which character applies these effects does not matter as the talent applies to their basic attacks, skills and items. The status effects affected by this talent are: &lt;a href=\"Acid%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Acid&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bleeding%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Bleeding&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Death%20Wish\"&gt;Death Wish&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Entangled%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Entangled&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Necrofire%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Necrofire&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rupture%20Tendons\"&gt;Ruptured Tendons&lt;/a&gt;.\nOut of all the 3 status effects, two are exclusive to skills. The &lt;a href=\"Rupture%20Tendons\"&gt;Ruptured Tendons&lt;/a&gt; status effect is exclusive to &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Scoundrel\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; skill &lt;a href=\"Rupture%20Tendons\"&gt;Rupture Tendons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Death%20Wish\"&gt;Death Wish&lt;/a&gt; status effect is exclusive to &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; skills of the same name and &lt;a href=\"Entangled%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Entangled&lt;/a&gt; status effect is exclusive to &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; skill &lt;a href=\"Worm%20Tremor\"&gt;Worm Tremor&lt;/a&gt;. Note that the &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; status effect will be applied to all &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; characters regardless of their Magic Armour values as it restores their Vitality.\nThis talent affects only the character that has picked it up and does not extend to their companions or their summoned entities/totems."}
{"id": "2273", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2273", "title": "Toshan", "text": "Toshan is one of Lord &lt;a href=\"Lovis\"&gt;Lovis&lt;/a&gt;' angry slaves, prisoners and enemies that will try\u00a0to kill &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; when he/she is teleported to the dungeon of &lt;a href=\"Lovis%27%20Tower\"&gt;Lovis' Tower&lt;/a&gt; after activating the Lovis' Scrying Stone.\nBackground.\nToshan used to be servant of Lord Lovis who had imprisoned him in dungeons beneath his Tower. Over the time in the dungeons he has grown insane and when he sees the player he believes he sees his former master Lovis, who came to taunt him, regardless of the main characters gender. Since he believes the player is Lovis he will after short conversation proceed to kill the player regardless of their response."}
{"id": "12382", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12382", "title": "Totems of the Necromancer", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Necromancer\"&gt;master Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sourcery%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;source&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a summoning necromancer source skill that allows caster to conjure bone totem at the feet of any living or dead hostile characters in 13 meter radius for 4 turns. The totems have no Physical Armour or Magic Armour and deal physical damage with its basic ranged attacks. The totems have only 1 Action Point and as such will only attack once per turn. \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Necromancy\"&gt;Necromancy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. The projectiles of Bone Totems are reflected back when their target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; (Definitive Edition). If the only available target is under such barrier the Totems will skip their turn.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 5 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 3 free memory slots. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 3000 gold. Since is a master Necromancer skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 16.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a summoning skill and as such it is primarily affected by Level, &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; ability of the caster. Due to the bone totems relying heavily on physical attacks and skills it also receives large bonus from Warfare ability. The Bone Totems begin to receive points into Warfare when caster is level 2. Following table shows at which level the totem receives points into Warfare.\n properties can be affected by talents and skills.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell necromancer spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. Out of these only \"&lt;a href=\"Tarquin\"&gt;Tarquin&lt;/a&gt;\" is guaranteed to follow the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; as they travel with &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;. \"&lt;a href=\"Jahan\"&gt;Jahan&lt;/a&gt;\" may join the Godwoken on the ship as well if his demands are met. "}
