{"id": "7160", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7160", "title": "Trife", "text": "The Trife is a creature living at &lt;a href=\"Homestead\"&gt;the End of Time&lt;/a&gt; in 4 AR.\nBackground.\nHe lived in the First Garden. When &lt;a href=\"the%20Godbox\"&gt;the Godbox&lt;/a&gt; which had the &lt;a href=\"Void%20Dragon\"&gt;Void Dragon&lt;/a&gt; in it was kept in the First Garden, the Trife waited for the chance to free the Evil. He allured &lt;a href=\"Astarte\"&gt;Astarte&lt;/a&gt; to open the Godbox, and the &lt;a href=\"Void%20Dragon\"&gt;Void Dragon&lt;/a&gt; was set free. After then, he was exiled from the God's realm, and has been living in &lt;a href=\"Homestead\"&gt;the End of Time&lt;/a&gt; since now.\nYou fight him before the final battle with the &lt;a href=\"Void%20Dragon\"&gt;Void Dragon&lt;/a&gt;. If you choose not to cure the Soul Forge between &lt;a href=\"Leandra\"&gt;Leandra&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Icara\"&gt;Icara&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Leandra\"&gt;Leandra&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"Death%20Princes\"&gt;Death Princes&lt;/a&gt; join the fight.\nBe aware that the Trife's air resistance is 100, so you can't do any damage to him with by &lt;a href=\"Jahan\"&gt;Jahan&lt;/a&gt; or other mage characters. He has low resistance, but it's not wise to handle him with weapons as he is healed by them (absorbs the damage)."}
{"id": "22825", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22825", "title": "Trigger Spores (Original Sin 2)", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;tierless Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; released as part of in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; skill that allows caster to make nearby Contamination Spores to explode. Each Spore deals poison damage to all characters. Additionaly the Spore will leave a Poison Cloud at its location.\nCharacters without Magic Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 3 turns and suffer damage directly to their health, with the exception of &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; who will receive &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; status effect regardless of their armour values and restore their health in proportion to the poison damage dealt by the status.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Geomancy\"&gt;Geomancy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nSkillbook and Scroll.\n is a tierless skill that has no scroll or skillbook from which it can be learnt or cast. \nInstead this skill can be learnt by either having an elven character eat an &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Scion%27s%20Arm\"&gt;Elven Scion's Arm&lt;/a&gt; which is dropped by &lt;a href=\"Daeyena\"&gt;Daeyena&lt;/a&gt; (earliest location at a ship in the &lt;a href=\"Hidden%20Alcove\"&gt;Hidden Alcove&lt;/a&gt;) or by reading &lt;a href=\"Spore%20Research%20Notes\"&gt;Spore Research Notes&lt;/a&gt; found in &lt;a href=\"the%20Blackpits\"&gt;the Blackpits&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "13075", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13075", "title": "Trinculo Shortfuse", "text": " is a councilor in \"\", representing the Imps.\nBackground.\nTrinculo Shortfuse first arrives on the Raven with the rest of the Councillors, representing Impish political interests. As an Imp, he is particularly interested in anything that would advance science and technology, but has much less input in topics outside of this range, at one point even deciding his position by flipping a coin. He doesn't consistently side with anyone.\nTrinculo is a relative of &lt;a href=\"Grumio\"&gt;Grumio&lt;/a&gt;, the Raven's resident inventor. In the post-victory scene, he's the only councilor not present in the throne room. He can instead be found next to Grumio in the workshop.\nTrinculo explains the absence of an Imp princess by telling the Commander that she exploded before she was able to arrive."}
