{"id": "2476", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2476", "title": "Turgoyn", "text": "Turgoyn is a historian initially found in the east coast &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%20Island%20Encampment\"&gt;Encampment&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%20Island\"&gt;Sentinel Island&lt;/a&gt; in 1300 AD.\nBackground.\nHe is a member of &lt;a href=\"Prancing%20Seahorse\"&gt;The Prancing Seahorse&lt;/a&gt;, a club consisting of scholars and historians, and he calls himself a \"maritime historian extraordinaire.\" The sinking of his ship, ironically, made him dream come true because the island is very rich in maritime history as there are many wrecks around their camp.\nTurgoyn is particularly interested in a ship which is found atop of a huge tree. He believes it is Ulfmar's ship: a legendary pirate who, all of the sudden, disappeared."}
{"id": "12319", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12319", "title": "Turn to Oil", "text": "Turn To Oil is a &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; skill in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive mixed skill that allows caster to transform all types of blood and water surfaces (with the exception of cursed frozen blood surface) into oil surfaces which will retain their blessed/cursed effects. Besides surface transformation this skill will remove &lt;a href=\"Stunned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Stunned&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shocked%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Shocked&lt;/a&gt; status effects from one chosen allied character in 13 meter range from the caster.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Geomancy\"&gt;Geomancy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Metamorphosis\"&gt;Metamorphosis&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into both &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 190 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a any non-source &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks are combined. Since is a mixed skill, traders do not have the skillbook for sale.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nSkill Modifiers.\nSince skill does not deal damage and only removes status effects besides transforming surfaces it is not affected by Level, attributes or abilities of the caster.\nHowever the skill may be affected by talents or other skills.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nThis skill cannot be bought or stolen from NPCs in the game."}
